title: best-ever stuffed peppers(serves 6)
directions: Wash peppers thoroughly; remove tops, seeds and membranes. Chop tops. Heat oil in large skillet; saute beef, onion and pepper tops over medium heat until meat is browned. Stir in corn, salt, pepper and basil. Turn into large bowl; clean skillet. Arrange peppers in skillet; fill with meat mixture. Sprinkle with cheese; pour soup and water over all. Cover; simmer for 40 minutes or until tender. Serve with noodles.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Crush crackers.
Trim fat from pork chops and slice edges. Put meat tenderizer on both sides and let sit for 1 hour.
Dip in milk, then cracker crumbs.
Put in greased pan.
Dot with Crisco. Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: creamy cucumber salad
directions: Mix dressing and pepper in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, onions, cheese and mayonnaise.
Put in casserole and top with crackers.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: pink delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: tiny pigs in a blanket
directions: Cut biscuits in half and spread out.
Roll Little Smokies in biscuits.
Cook at 375° until biscuits are golden brown.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Place all ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: no peek stew
directions: Mix meat, chopped vegetables, and seasonings in a pot. Combine tomato juice cocktail and V-8 juice; dissolve tapioca in juices. Pour over meat and vegetable mixture. Cover and bake 5 hours in 250°oven. Do not peek! Serve with cornbread and green salad.

title: fat-free dip for fresh strawberries
directions: Whip together.
Serve in a bowl surrounded by fresh strawberries.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix cranberry juice with orange juice concentrate.
Add carbonated liquids just before serving.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Mix beef, rice, onion and seasonings. Form into small balls. Fry in oil until lightly brown.
Add tomato sauce and water. Cover and simmer over medium-low heat for 45 minutes.

title: yummy dessert
directions: Mix together butter, walnuts and flour.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and whipped topping.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix together puddings and milk.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Cool.
Top with nondairy whipped topping and nuts when set.

title: broccoli-rice casserole(large recipe - better to halve it.)
directions: Arrange in layers in a 2 1/2-quart casserole in the order given, beginning with rice.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Line 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch loaf pan with foil.
Mix together first 6 ingredients to moisten.
Add beef and celery, mixing with hands until well blended.
Put into pan and shape into a loaf. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: lemon chicken medallions
directions: Cut chicken into medallions.
Mix flour, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Dredge and coat meat pieces.
Heat oil in skillet. Fry meat until golden brown.
Remove meat and place in oven at low temperature to keep warm.

title: pearl huffman's light rolls
directions: Add a little of the sugar to the warm water.
Add yeast and dissolve real well.
Add remaining ingredients and make a soft dough.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Work down and make into rolls.
To make rolls, pinch off dough about the size of an egg. Roll dough between both hands to the shape of a hot dog.
Place close together in a loaf pan.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° about 20 minutes.

title: pudding delight
directions: Mix flour, walnuts, sugar and margarine; put in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip; press in pan.
Mix pudding and milk; spread on as next layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: delicious potato salad
directions: Mix and chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; cool.
When cool, stir in vinegar and mayonnaise; beat until smooth.
Stir in onion, celery and eggs.
Take corned beef from can; put in colander and run hot water over corned beef, melting away the fat.
Break corned beef in 1 inch pieces and then add to the gelatin mixture.
Chill in refrigerator until set.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine ingredients in order given, mixing well. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour to blend flavors.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Blend in cooled chocolate.
Add the vanilla, then add eggs, one at a time, beating for 5 minutes after each addition.
Pour into baked shell and refrigerate overnight. When ready to serve, top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: sweet nothings
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Place Rice Chex in largest bowl you can find.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal.
Carefully stir until well coated.
Pour powdered sugar into a small plastic garbage bag.
Scrape the gooey cereal mixture into the bag.
Hold the top of the bag closed with your hand and gently shake to coat all of the cereal pieces.
Store in tins or glass jars.

title: ham salad spread
directions: Cream together cream cheese and salad dressing.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: quick orange drop danish
directions: Stir dry ingredients together, mixing thoroughly.
Add milk to form a stiff dough.
Drop by heaping tablespoonful onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden.
While baking, prepare icing.
Spread on danish while hot.
Yields 6 danish.

title: heavenly strawberry dessert
directions: Crumble the vanilla wafers in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Save 1/2 cup to garnish with.
Mix the butter, powdered sugar and eggs until fluffy; spread carefully over crumbs.
Slice the strawberries; place on top.
Cover top with Cool Whip.
Cover with plastic wrap; chill overnight.

title: baked brie
directions: Place Brie in oven on serving dish.
Sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Let cool a little as the minute you cut into cheese, it will run.
Serve with crackers.
Delicious!

title: date balls
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and dates and cool slightly. Add egg, blending well. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Cool slightly. Stir in vanilla, cereal and nuts. Form into small balls and roll in coconut. Be careful; mixture is very hot.

title: 3 step cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with mixer on medium speed until well blended. Add eggs, mixing until blended.

title: indonesian shrimp sate
directions: Heat oil in small skillet over low heat.
Add garlic and cook until lightly browned.
Stir in all ingredients except shrimp. Cook 1 minute.
Let cool.
Add shrimp and mix with fingers until well coated.

title: corn pone pie
directions: Cook hamburger and onion, then add tomatoes, Worcestershire, chili powder and salt.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add beans.
Put into greased pan and put corn bread batter (your own recipe or mix) on top.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package; drain and set aside. Mix celery, onions, cheese and mayonnaise.
Then add vegetables and mix well.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Top with crumbs and drizzle with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot sauce for chicken wings
directions: Deep fry or bake chicken wings.
Cover with hot sauce and serve.
Use less Tabasco sauce if you don't want sauce as hot.

title: sandwich ring
directions: Form a circle with the French bread dough, seam side down, on a baking stone or cookie sheet.
With a pastry brush, apply butter and garlic powder mixture to top of dough.
Bake dough as directed on package.
Cool and slice ring.
Layer cheese, meat, lettuce, onion, tomato and dressing.
Replace top of ring; slice and serve.

title: tuna surprise
directions: Mix together ingredients to desired consistency.
May be eaten as is or spread on bread or rolls warmed in microwave or conventional oven to melt cheese.

title: rebecca's ritz bits
directions: Combine oleo, sugar and Karo.
Cook until it comes to a boil. Cook for 5 minutes and take off heat.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over pecans and Ritz Bits.
Bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 10 minutes.
Pour out on wax paper and separate.

title: little cheese cakes
directions: Beat
ingredients well.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in cupcake shell. Fill 2/3 full with mixture.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: apple-nut bread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add the dry ingredients, then the apples and walnuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch bread pan.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Boil chicken, remove skin and bones, cut into bite size pieces and return to chicken stock.
Mix ingredients.
Roll out dough and cut into strips.
Bring stock to a boil and put strips of dough into the boiling stock.
Cover pot and cook for 20 minutes or until dumplings appear done.

title: crab melt
directions: Melt butter (or margarine) and cheese over low heat, add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt; mix well.
Process in blender until smooth.
In bowl fold in crabmeat and pimentos.
Mix well.
Slice bread into 1/2 inch slices and spread with crab mixture.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve immediately.
Makes 20 slices.

title: oatmeal fudge cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, butter, milk and cocoa; bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from stove.
Quickly add 2 cups oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix.
Drop onto waxed paper 1 tablespoon at a time to form cookies.
Let cool and serve.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef into narrow strips.
Melt butter in skillet and add meat and onions.
Cook and stir until meat browns.
Lower heat; add mushrooms and more butter, if needed.
Cook 10 minutes.
Remove mixture from skillet and set aside.
To skillet juices add remaining butter, flour and seasonings.
Add sour cream, slowly blending until smooth.
Add meat mixture and heat through (add water if needed).
Serve with noodles.
Top with chives.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add coconut, raisins, oatmeal and pecans.
Mix well. Add vanilla and mix well.
Drop by the half teaspoonful onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.
These are very good and always make a bit hit!

title: chunky chicken salad
directions: Prepare noodles; drain.
In large bowl, combine noodles, corn, red pepper, mushrooms, olives, celery, onion and cheese.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and margarine.
(Reserve 1/2 cup mixture for top.)
Press into greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Add creme de menthe to marshmallow.
Mix until blended at low speed.
Fold in whipped cream.
(I imagine you could use Pyrex pie plate for this, but works beautifully in spring-form pan.)

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Lightly butter a 9-inch square pan.
In a large heat-resistant bowl, stir together the chocolate and marshmallow cream; set aside.
In a 3-quart heavy saucepot, mix the sugar, milk and butter, stirring to combine well.
Over low heat, gradually bring the mixture to a boil, stirring until the sugar dissolves.
Dip a pastry brush in cold water and wash down the sides of the pot. Continue to boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly without touching the sides of the pot.

title: jiffy cake
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan. Sprinkle cake mix over fruit and cut up margarine into pads and place over cake mix.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crisp oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll out in 2 rolls about 18-inches long. Put
in
wax
paper
and
refrigerate until chilled. Slice and bake
until golden brown.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate crinkles(cookies)
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and granulated sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time.
Add vanilla.
Measure flour by sifting.
Stir flour into oil mixture.
Chill overnight or for several hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drop into confectioners sugar.
Roll into balls.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes; mix other ingredients and pour over potatoes. Bake at 450° until brown.

title: wings recipe #3 fly away soup
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring the 2 cups of water, bouillon cubes and raw vegetables to a boil.
Add the chicken wings and boil until done and the meat can be easily removed from the bone. Chicken is done when a fork can be easily inserted and removed and the juices run clear.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Beat egg in bowl. Add chicken and toss until coated.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup cornstarch; toss until all pieces are coated.
Melt shortening in a large skillet. Add chicken.
Cook until brown. Remove from skillet. Add enough water to reserved syrup to make 1 cup.
Stir liquid, vinegar and sugar into skillet.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Stir in green pepper and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 minutes.
Blend water and 2 tablespoons cornstarch until mixture thickens and boils. Boil and stir 1 minute. Stir in pineapple, soy sauce, carrots and chicken.
Heat.
Serve on rice. Sprinkle with green onion.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and chill 4 to 6 hours. Serve.

title: hamburger dish
directions: Fry hamburger and onion, drain off fat.
Add rest of ingredients, simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over toast or hot biscuits.

title: sauerkraut and sausage bake
directions: In skillet, brown sausage; drain off fat.
Stir together sauerkraut and green onions.
Turn into a 1 1/2 quart casserole. Spoon sausage over sauerkraut mixture.
Prepare mashed potatoes according to package directions.
Stir 2 tablespoons of the cheese into potatoes.
Spread potatoes over sausage; sprinkle remaining 2 tablespoons cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° until heated through, 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: black bean and corn salad
directions: Heat oil in frying pan.
Add the onion, pepper and garlic. Cover pan; reduce heat to low and cook for 3 or 4 minutes or until onion and pepper have softened.
Lightly crush the cumin seed and stir into vegetables.
Cook for another 30 seconds.
Rinse the black beans.
Put the corn and 1 tablespoon of its liquid in a bowl.
Add the beans, the pepper mixture and the vinegar and toss gently.
Season to taste with salt and cayenne.
Serves 5 or 6 as a side dish.
Very colorful salad; good on buffet with Mexican or Tex-Mex food.

title: pecan pie custard style(makes 2 pies)
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Cook for 10 minutes on 400°. Turn down to 350° and cook for 35 minutes more or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Custard will be a bit shaky, but will thicken as it cools.

title: flank steak fix-up
directions: Rub steak with garlic; season with 1 teaspoon salt and the pepper.
Cut meat crosswise into 4 to 6 serving pieces.
In large skillet, partially cook bacon.
Drain.
Reserve drippings in skillet.
Place slice of bacon on each piece of meat; roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Coat rolls with flour.
Brown rolls in reserved drippings over medium heat.
Stir together tomato sauce, 1/2 teaspoon salt, marjoram leaves, parsley and onion; pour over meat.
Cover tightly; simmer 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In casserole bowl, combine soup and pepper.
Stir in beans and 2/3 cup French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Stir.
Sprinkle remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes or until onions are golden.

title: boursin cheese
directions: Blend together and chill well.
Sprinkle with coarse black pepper.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: chunky greek salad
directions: In large serving bowl, with fork, combine oil, lemon juice, salt and black pepper.
Add tomatoes, cucumbers, red pepper, green onion, olives, and mint. Toss until evenly mixed.
If not serving right away, cover and refrigerate up to 6 hours.
Sprinkle with feta to serve if you like.
Toss before serving.

title: quickie dinner
directions: Cook large package of salisbury steak according to directions. Stir in frozen vegetables.
Cook 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Place biscuits on top of mixture and cook until golden brown.
Dip with slotted spoon.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken roux
directions: Boil chicken until done with chopped celery and bell pepper. Salt and pepper to taste.
Make roux of oil and flour.
Make roux real brown (almost burned).
Add onion, sliced.
Add to chicken. Cook until done.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, lemon peel, butter, lemon juice, milk and egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Cover and cool.
Fold in sour cream. Pour into baked pastry shell.
Chill for 2 hours or more before serving.
Top with whipped cream.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown the beef and onion in skillet.
Add the rice and beans. Add salt, chili powder and garlic salt to taste.
Cook together. Simmer and top with grated cheese; heat until melted.

title: walking tostitos
directions: Using a large platter, spread the ingredients according to the order listed (except the tortilla chips and salsa sauce).
Chill in refrigerator for one hour.
When ready to serve, pour salsa sauce over and insert tortilla chips around the edges of platter.

title: nana's oyster dressing
directions: Mix broth,
bouillon
cubes
and
oleo; let stand until bouillon cubes can	be
broken
up.
Break	all the bread into small pieces;
put	in large pan.
Add celery and onions.
Add sage and stir;
add
broth	and mix well.
(Chop oysters.) Add oysters, liquid and
eggs;	mix.
Adjust salt to taste.
There should be enough
liquid
to see after standing a few minutes. Bake in covered
roaster
pan
at
350° about 2 hours or until done.
Serves 8 hungry people.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry nut pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature and whip until fluffy. Add milk and beat well.
Add lemon juice and vanilla; blend well. Add cherries, halved or quartered, and the nuts.
Pour into crust and chill 3 or more hours.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until smooth.
Pour in milk.
Fold in lemon juice.
Pour in crust and chill.

title: peach cobbler in 10 minutes
directions: Drain peaches and pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Mix baking mix with shortening, milk, egg and sugar in a bowl. Mix by hand until consistency of pancake batter and pour over peaches. Bake at 350° until brown.
Can use other fruit or add nutmeg, cinnamon or raisins for extra ummp.

title: spicy chicken soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients, except pinto beans.
Bring to boil over high heat; reduce heat.
Cover. Simmer 45 to 55 minutes or until flavors are blended together and chicken is tender.
Add pinto beans.
Continue simmering 20 minutes.
Makes 10 (1-cup) servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Saute hamburger and salt.
A little chopped onion may be added. Mix the potatoes, soup and sour cream with 1 1/2 cups of cheese all together with the meat.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with reserved 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake a few minutes more.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 375° and bake deep dish pie shell for 10 minutes while mixing pie ingredients.
Melt chocolate chips and butter, stirring constantly.
Add all other ingredients.
At this time you can mix nuts into pie mixture or sprinkle on top (maybe 1/2 with nuts and 1/2 without).
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Turn oven down to 325° and bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until set.
Cool and garnish with Cool Whip.
Enjoy!

title: out of this world pie
directions: Combine first four ingredients; bring to a boil and cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O sugar-free. Strawberry or banana flavor is good.
Cool completely and add a little red food coloring and 4 banana slices.
Mix and pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream before serving.

title: pizza-a-la-rice
directions: Combine rice, eggs, and cheese in a bowl.
Press firmly into bottom of 12-inch greased pizza pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes. Top pizza-rice crust with onion and favorite pizza toppings.
Mix in a small bowl the tomato sauce, oregano, basil and salt; place on top of pizza.
Top with cheese topping.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan in oven.
Mix Bisquick, paprika, salt and pepper. Coat chicken with this mixture.
Place skin down in pan.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.
Turn and bake another 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix chocolate mix, eggs, milk and cornstarch in saucepan. Heat to boiling.
Cook until thick.
Pour in baked pie shell. Refrigerate until firm.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare, core and slice apples.
Line a pie plate with pastry. Fill with apples.
Sprinkle with sugar, bits of butter and cinnamon.
Put on upper crust and prick.
Bake in hot oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 425° until crust is brown and fruit is soft.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Mix until well blended. Add egg.
Beat until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix until blended.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift together flour, salt, sugar and baking soda. Mix the pumpkin, oil, eggs, water and spices together, then combine with the dry ingredients, but do not mix too thoroughly. Stir in the nuts. Pour into well buttered loaf pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes until straw comes out clean. Turn out of the pan and cool on a rack.

title: fig pie
directions: Heat first five ingredients in a saucepan.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Place top crust on pie, cutting slits for escape of steam.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: italian style marinated vegetables
directions: Thaw carrots, cauliflower, green beans and drain.
Pour dressing over thawed vegetables.
Add pimentos.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Drain.
Combine vegetable mixture with cheese and mix lightly.
Sprinkle with additional cheese before serving.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients 5 minutes from the time it starts to boil.
Remove from heat and add 1 package cherry jello.
Let stand until cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: shrimp pilau
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oleo. Add shrimp; stir until pink. Add consomme, rice and season.
Steam until done.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In large bowl, combine first 3 ingredients.
Microwave on High for 3 1/2 minutes.
Stir, then continue heating at 30 second intervals until melted.
Do not exceed 5 minutes.
Average cooking time:
4 to 4 1/2 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in 9 x 9-inch pan. Place in refrigerator to cool.

title: one pot pork chops
directions: Salt, pepper and flour pork chops.
Brown chops in small amount of oil in large skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add green peppers, onions and canned tomatoes.
If using raw yams, add them now.
If using canned yams, simmer the chops, covered, 30 minutes or until done, then add sweet potatoes and heat through.

title: quick tamale pie
directions: Mix cornmeal with cold water.
Add hot water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook over low heat 20 minutes.
Brown beef, onions and chili.
Mix olives with cooked cornmeal.
Spread 1/2 of cornmeal mixture in baking dish.
Add meat mixture.
Cover with rest of cornmeal mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: little smokies in a blanket
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Cover broiler type pan (can be cookie sheet with rack inserts) with aluminum foil.
Make several holes for grease to drain.
Wrap Little Smokies each with one strip of bacon. Secure each with a toothpick and place on the pan.
Now cover completely with brown sugar and place pan in oven.
Bake a half hour, then transfer to another pan to continue baking.
Do this by lifting foil.
Bake until brown sugar is caramelized.
Baking time is about an hour.
(Found pan transfer necessary because of amount of grease; you may use your own ideas.)
These are guaranteed to disappear.
No leftovers.
May need to make more, we did.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all but 1/2 of onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Use rest of onions on top.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Soak gelatine in cold water.
Grind cranberries.
Mix cranberries, sugar, marshmallows, pecans and boiling water.
Mix with soaked gelatine.
Mix thoroughly.
Use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Let cool before serving.

title: hot mulled apple punch
directions: Bring to a boil, then simmer 2 hours.
Enjoy!

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli with eggs, cream of mushroom soup, cheese and mayonnaise.
Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Cut chicken into nugget size. Beat eggs slightly. Dip chicken nuggets into egg; drain off. Roll in bread crumbs. Melt margarine in pan; fry chicken in margarine until done. Put chicken in baking dish. Pour chicken broth over chicken; cover with Muenster cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Boil chicken parts until done; save liquid.
Chop.
Mix with rice and all other ingredients.
Stir well.
Put in baking dish. Pour liquid over rice and bake for 30 minutes.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Place chicken in a large resealable plastic bag. Add cornstarch and toss to coat. Combine soy sauce, ginger and garlic powder. Add to bag and shake well. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: soft spice biscotti
directions: Preheat oven at 375 degrees.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Place thick layer of potatoes in greased large baking dish. Add layer of macaroni.
Break up ground meat evenly over top.
Add layer of onion, green pepper and carrots.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and sugar over top; add tomatoes.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Top with cheese and bake 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: sausage bread
directions: Allow bread dough to thaw in refrigerator overnight and roll into three 9 x 13-inch rectangles.
Sprinkle onion, cooked sausage and cheese down the middle and fold each side to the middle and seal all edges.
Place seam side down on foil-lined cookie sheet and let rise 30 minutes.
Follow package directions for cooking bread.
When done, cool 10 to 15 minutes and slice.

title: candy cane sugar cookies
directions: Mix cookie dough as on package for drop cookies.
Use one measuring tablespoon of dough for each cookie.
Divide dough into 7 balls, roll some in red sugar, some in white sugar, place on baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 375 degrees for 7 - 8 minutes.

title: miniature peanut butter treats
directions: Combine butter, sugars, egg, peanut butter and vanilla in mixing bowl; beat until smooth.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Cover dough and chill.
When cold enough to handle easily, roll in small (walnut-sized) balls; place each ball in paper lined miniature muffin tin.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Remove from oven; gently press 1 peanut butter cup into each cookie to make depression.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool on rack.
Store in cool place until serving time.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat until smooth.
Cover and chill.

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel apples and cut in small pieces.
Peel bananas and slice in small pieces.
Drain pineapple and peaches, reserving juice. Slice strawberries and mix all fruit together.
Add pudding mix to juices; stir until thickened.
Mix with fruit mixture and chill.

title: chicken, broccoli, rice, and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a medium saucepan bring water to a boil. Mix in instant rice; cover and remove from heat. Let sit for 5 minutes. In a 9X13 inch baking dish, mix the prepared rice, chicken, cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, butter, milk, broccoli, onion and processed cheese. Bake in oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until cheese is melted. Stir halfway through cooking to help cheese melt evenly.

title: applesauce-raisin bread
directions: Mix the applesauce, oil and sugar. Sift in the flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Mix well after each addition. Add the slightly beaten egg and raisins.
Mix, then pour into a greased and floured 8 x 4-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: chicken supreme
directions: After stewing chicken, remove meat from broth (when cool), bone and dice.
Set aside.
Cook noodles in broth according to package directions.
Drain.
Mix onions, pimento, oregano and a dash of pepper and soup.
Add milk.
Stir together and add chicken, drained noodles and half of the grated cheese to soup mixture.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with remaining grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix well and form into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, syrup and melted butter. Combine and add pecans, vanilla and salt.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° about 1 hour. Also sometimes I chop the pecans instead of leaving them halved.

title: roland's macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil noodles until tender; drain.
Pour 1/3 noodles into 13 x 9-inch ovenproof dish or an elongated casserole dish.
Add a layer of 1/4-inch sliced cheese.
Repeat procedure, ending with a layer of cheese.
Crumble crackers on top.
Mix butter and milk; pour over dish.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Delicious!

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix together the brown sugar, white sugar, eggs, cooking oil and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, corn flakes and salt and add to wet ingredients.
Add pecans, raisins and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Makes 15 dozen cookies.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix together.
Allow to stand at least 1 day before serving with raw vegetables.

title: zucchini fried patties
directions: Mix together in a large bowl all of the above ingredients. Drop by spoonful into hot greased pan.
Brown on each side, approximately 1 1/2 to 2 minutes per side.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Bring to a boil in saucepan on direct heat the water or milk, sugar, salt and lemon peel; add cornstarch.
Cook over low heat until thickened, about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add egg yolks, butter and lemon juice separately, mixing well each time.
Pour into an 8-inch baked or crumb crust pie shell.
Top with meringue; brown.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions using 5 cups milk. Fold in sour cream and one tub Cool Whip.
Layer pudding, cookies and bananas in dish and top with remaining tub of Cool Whip.

title: cabbage pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Make a pie crust for 9-inch bottom and top.
Cook and stir hamburg in pan until brown; drain.
In same pan, add margarine until melted.
Stir in onions; cook until soft. Slowly add cabbage; cook until tender, 20 minutes.
Stir in egg and rest of ingredients into cabbage mixture.
Set aside.
Prepare pie crust.
Line pie pan; add filling.
Put on top crust, crimp edges and cut holes on top.
Bake 20 minutes to 1/2 hour or until crust is brown.

title: green eggs
directions: Spray a cake pan with Pam.
Layer Jack cheese on bottom.
Top with chilies.
Combine eggs with sour cream.
Put on green chilies.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, or until set.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in an unbaked pie shell at 300° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Bake in well-greased and floured loaf pan for 40 minutes or longer, if necessary, at 350°.

title: light veggie dip
directions: In blender or food processor, chop onion until saucy.
Add bouillon cube and cream cheese; blend together, then add mayonnaise.
Blend until all is dissolved. Chill.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients 3 times.
Add nuts and raisins to flour.
In large mixing bowl, beat oil and eggs.
Mix carrots to flour mixture.
Beat 3 1/2 minutes on medium speed.
Turn into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan or 2 (9 x 12-inch) round baking pans.
Bake in a 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes for a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, until done.
For a 9-inch pan, bake in a 325° oven for 40 minutes or until done.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: punch
directions: Mix
all
ingredients (except sherbet) in a large punch bowl. Add ice just before serving.
Spoon sherbet on top.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake sweet potatoes at 400° for about 1 hour or until tender. Let cool to touch, peel and mash sweet potatoes. Beat mashed sweet potatoes, sugar and next 5 ingredients at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth. Spoon potato mixture into a greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish. Combine cornflakes and next 3 ingredients in a small bowl. Sprinkle diagonally over casserole in rows 2 inches apart. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven; let stand 10 minutes. Sprinkle alternate rows with marshmallows; bake 10 additional minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: lemon pie
directions: Put water and vinegar in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Beat together egg yolks, flour and sugar.
Add a small amount of boiling liquid and blend well.
Stir mixture quickly into boiling liquid and continue to cook and stir until thick.
Remove from heat and add Blair lemon flavoring, butter and salt.
Pour into baked shells.
Makes 2 pies.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Put on pies, being careful to seal edges. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes until browned.

title: congealed shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Add soup and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Add cream cheese and melt, then remove from fire.
To shrimp, add mayonnaise, celery, onions and remaining ingredients.
Grease mold with butter very well.
Pour into mold and refrigerate for at least 24 hours.
To unmold, dip in sink of warm water.
Serve with crackers.

title: fresh apple cake ii
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Dough will be stiff.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: marinated coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrots, celery and green pepper. Mix all other ingredients in a blender. Pour over cabbage, mixing together. Coat well. Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: coconut custard impossible pie
directions: Blend all together in blender for 2 minutes.
Pour into 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool to serve.

title: chunky chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour and baking soda in small bowl.
Set aside.
Put the margarine in a large mixing bowl and beat at medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add both kinds of sugar and beat until mixed well (about 1 minute).
Add egg and vanilla to sugar mixture.
Beat.
Add flour mixture gradually, beating (on low speed) after each addition.

title: hot fudge ice cream sauce
directions: Melt margarine with cocoa over low heat.
Mix in sugar then milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often until begins to thicken.
Add vanilla.
It will thicken more as it cools.

title: easy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients in bowl together and mix.
Pour into ungreased pan.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix cocoa into dry cake mix.
Add other ingredients by directions on cake mix.
Pour into 3 pans that have been sprayed with Pam.
Cool cakes.
Cream sifted powdered sugar with cream cheese and softened butter.
Add vanilla.
Mix well and spread on cake.

title: charlie's cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450° (350° for gas stove).
Combine ingredients in large mixing bowl and stir.
The bread will rise higher if mixed manually.
Pour into a greased pan; cook for about 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: bacon wrap-ups
directions: You will need 33 wooden toothpicks.

title: eggless cake
directions: Butter a 9-inch square pan.
Line with wax paper and butter the paper.
Cream the butter and sugar; stir in the melted chocolate.
Sift flour and soda together and add to the first mixture alternately with sour milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn cake out onto rack and remove paper.
When cool, shake confectioners sugar over the top.
Cut into squares.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Place crab meat and cream cheese in a large bowl.
Mix on low speed until crab is shredded and cheese is well mixed with crab. Add Old Bay seasoning, cayenne pepper, half and half and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix for an additional minute.
Spread in shallow baking dish and top with Swiss cheese slices.
Bake at 400° until cheese is melted and bubbly around the edges, about 20 minutes.
Serve with bagel chips and lemon wedges.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg in a large bowl.
Stir in milk, corn and 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add and beat in flour, baking powder, nutmeg, salt and pepper.

title: potato patties
directions: In a bowl, combine mashed potatoes, finely chopped onion, flour and salt.
Shape into patties.
Cook in frying pan with a little cooking oil.
Turn only once; brown well.

title: fruit salad delight
directions: Drain all ingredients (bottled and canned). Whip the cream cheese until soft and creamy. Mix all ingredients and add sugar according to your taste. Refrigerate it for 4 hours or overnight.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix milk with instant pudding and beat for 1
to 2 minutes.
Spread over cream cheese.
Put remaining Cool Whip on top of last layer.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Cut approximately 15 to 18 squares.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Thinly slice cucumbers, onions, peppers and whole garlic cloves. Sprinkle with salt and put ice cubes on cucumbers. Let stand 3 hours. After 3 hours, drain. Discard salt water. Put cucumber in vinegar, sugar and spices. Bring to boiling point and seal in sterilized jars.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Combine cooking oil and sugar and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add hot water, then dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake in 3 greased (8-inch) layer cake pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with icing.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Add pudding, oil and cake mix.
Beat eggs and add to mix. Add orange juice, vodka and Galliano; mix well.
Bake in 10-inch angel food pan for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable pizza(makes 1 serving)
directions: Toast English muffin halves. Top each with vegetables and tomato sauce.
Heat in toaster oven or in preheated moderate oven (350°) for a few minutes or until bubbly hot.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Heat just until cheese melts and browns slightly.

title: apricot mold
directions: To the pineapple juice, add water to total 1 1/2 cups. Dissolve Jell-O with the 2 cups of boiling water.
Add pineapple juice.
Let Jell-O set until almost firm. Stir in sour cream and beat until smooth. Add crushed pineapple.
Mix and pour into mold.

title: heavenly orange salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Jell-O.
Drain oranges and pineapple. Blend together with Cool Whip.

title: vinegar cornmeal pie
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in unbaked 9-inch pie shell at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: nancy's squash
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine.
Add both kinds of squash and onion.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and salt to taste.
Cook until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add tomatoes and cook until done.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
This is very good served over rice.

title: chicken pie in potato crust
directions: In bowl, combine the potatoes, butter, salt and pepper. Press in greased 9 x 13 baking dish; set aside.

title: chicken cantalone
directions: On each piece of chicken, spread pepper, Italian seasoning and Dijon mustard.
Top each piece of chicken with a slice of cheese; roll up, secure with toothpick and then flour.
Saute in olive oil or butter over medium heat.
Cover with vegetables and cook slowly until tender.

title: sweet pickle spears
directions: Slice ends from cucumbers and cut into spears.
Pour boiling water over cucumbers; let stand 2 hours.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix 2 cups sugar, milk, egg yolks (save the whites) and flour in a boiler.
Place remaining cup of sugar in heavy skillet and caramelize it.
Then add this to the other ingredients that have been warming.
Cook until it thickens.
Add butter and vanilla. Put in uncooked pie shells.
Beat the egg whites and put on the pies.
Bake until the whites turn brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into 1-inch meatballs. Spray or lightly grease a baking dish with oil.
Place meatballs in dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tuna-rice pie
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, omitting salt; set aside.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well and set aside.
Combine rice and egg; mix well.
Press firmly on bottom and sides of a buttered 10x6x2-inch baking dish; set aside. Combine soup and Worcestershire sauce in a large sauce pan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in broccoli, mushrooms and tuna.
Pour into rice shell.
Cover and bake at 375 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: key lime pie
directions: Stir milk, lime juice and food coloring.
Fold in whipped topping. Pour in crust.
Refrigerate an hour or more.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in sweetened condensed milk, ReaLemon brand and food coloring, if desired.
Pour in prepared crust.
Bake 8 minutes.
Cool.
Chill thoroughly.
Top with whipped topping or whipped cream.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: reduced fat caesar salad
directions: Combine water and bouillon granules in container of an electric blender; process 30 seconds.
Add lemon juice and next 6 ingredients.
With blender running, gradually add olive oil in a slow steady stream.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
To serve, shake dressing vigorously and drizzle over lettuce.
Add garlic croutons and Parmesan cheese; toss.
This recipe has 8 grams of fat per serving compared to 36 grams of fat per serving in traditional Caesar salads.

title: zucchini balls(appetizer)
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Form into balls.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes or freeze before baking for later use.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together, put in pans and bake for a while, about 1 hour I think.

title: zippy beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir meat until brown.
Drain off excess fat.
Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
In ungreased 2-quart casserole, mix all ingredients except chips.
Cover; bake 40 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with chips and bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pie pastry
directions: Mix all dry ingredients with fork until particles are size of pea.
Add water; roll on floured board until size you want.

title: candied apple salad
directions: Over medium heat, stir crushed pineapple with juice, egg, flour, apple cider vinegar and sugar until thick.
Refrigerate until cool.
Peel and dice apples, then mix with pineapple mixture, 1/2 cup peanuts and Cool Whip.
Mix well and spread in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup peanuts on top.
Refrigerate. Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: banana salad
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly; cool. Add Cool Whip.
Slice bananas and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Put in layers:
bananas, whipped topping and ground peanuts.

title: ice cream sundae pie
directions: Allow ice cream to soften or stir with spoon until pliable. Spoon into ready crust.
Cover and freeze until firm, about 3 hours.
Serve pie wedges with chocolate fudge topping, whipped cream and cherries.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: Prepare linguini according to package directions.
Drain.
In heavy saucepan, heat butter and oil.
Saute garlic and clams over medium heat, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in parsley, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add hot cooked linguini to clam mixture; toss lightly.
Serve on warm platter.
Parmesan cheese is optional.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Mix together all ingredients and seal tightly in pan with aluminum foil.
Bake in 300° oven for 3 hours.
Do not open until cooking time is over.
(If adding vegetables, may also want to add 1 can cream of mushroom soup.)
Great main dish for Sunday dinner.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir together.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in mixing bowl.
Beat egg yolks until frothy and add to butter and sugar mixture.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add alternately with the sour cream while beating at medium speed.
Add your choice of either 2 tbsp. lemon juice and grated rind, or 2 tbsp. rum, or tsp. vanilla.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff and fold into cake batter.
Pour mixture into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: real cajun red beans and rice
directions: Cook beans and pork in salted water slowly for 45 minutes. Add vegetables, seasonings and tomato sauce.
Cook slowly another hour, stirring occasionally.
Add sausage for extra body; cook 45 minutes more.
Cool, but do not necessarily refrigerate.
Reheat and bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer gently for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over boiled rice.
Less pepper may be used for a tender palate!

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix and mash the carrots, oleo, salt, flour, cheese, eggs and milk.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and nutmeg; add eggs, beating after each addition.
Stir in bananas and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat into creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in nuts, pour batter into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix eggs, vanilla, flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Add crushed pineapple and chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° from 30 to 35 minutes in a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan or two 9-inch round pans.

title: pate maison
directions: Combine water, peppercorns, whole cloves, bay leaves and parsley in a 4-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil, simmer 10 minutes and strain.
Add chicken livers to liquid.
Cook just below simmering point until liquid is clear and livers are done, about 10 minutes.
Drain livers and put once through food grinder.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, blend together remaining ingredients except brandy.
Add liver and mix until smooth.
Stir in brandy. Line a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with aluminum foil.
Pack pate into pan. Chill thoroughly before serving.
Flavor will develop more fully if allowed to chill overnight.

title: marinated rice salad
directions: Cook rice.
Add dressing and soy sauce and refrigerate overnight.
Three hours before serving, add rest of ingredients. Toss and refrigerate.
Can be doubled or tripled.

title: kraut balls
directions: Fry sausage, stirring constantly, so does not lump.
Pour off grease.
Drain on paper towels.
Mix onion, peppers, sage and parsley with sausage.
Add mustard, stir cream cheese over medium heat until melted.
Stir for 20 minutes.
If too moist, add bread crumbs.
Should be able to roll into sticky balls.
Cool in refrigerator overnight.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender in 2 1/2 quarts boiling salted water; drain.
Rinse with hot water.
Drain mushrooms, saving liquid.
Melt butter in saucepan; saute onion.
Add salt and mushroom liquid.
Blend in soups.
Stir until smooth and gradually add evaporated milk, stirring over heat until smooth and thickened.

title: calabaza con elote(squash and corn)
directions: To make Sofrito Sauce:
Saute in oil the onion, tomatoes, garlic, salt, pepper and cumin.

title: savory red beans and rice
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook and stir bacon until crisp. Reserve 1 teaspoon drippings in pan.
In necessary, add oil to make 1 teaspoon. Drain bacon on paper towel. Cook onion in drippings until tender but not brown. Add bacon, broth, uncooked rice, celery, salt, hot sauce and pepper.

Bring to a boil, then reduce heat. Cover and simmer 40 minutes. Add undrained beans and pepper strips. Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes more. Serve immediately. This is a low-fat (4 grams), low cholesterol (2 mg.) recipe.

title: pine-grape punch
directions: Combine juices and Sprite in a large punch bowl.
To this add water then ice to chill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Stir in zucchini.
Add flour mixture.
Don't overbeat.
Fold in chopped nuts (and raisins, if desired).
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.
Can also add chocolate chips to batter.

title: pizza
directions: Put the bread on a piece of card board.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix together
tomatoes, soups, garlic, chili powder and onion. Add boned
chicken
and
a
little
broth.
Pour
into casserole dish and
stick broken tortillas into mixture.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Top with cheese slices and put back into oven long enough to melt the cheese.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Stir in pan until boiling.
Serve over chicken, pork, etc.

title: philly 3-step cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Pour batter into pie crust. Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes, or until center is almost set. Cool.
Add fruit (strawberries, cherries or other choice) if you wish.
For best results, refrigerate for 3 hours before using.

title: barbara semchenko's broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, saute onion in oil.
Add broth and broccoli. Cook 5 minutes.
Add noodles and garlic.
Cook until noodles are done.
Add milk and Velveeta.
Cook until cheese melts.
Don't boil after milk is added.
Makes a lot!

title: corn relish
directions: Drop ears of corn in boiling water.
Boil 5 minutes.
Dip in cold water.
Cut from cob; measure.
Combine corn with remaining ingredients and boil 15 minutes.
Pack into sterilized jars to within 1/2-inch of top.
Put on cap; screw band firmly tight. Process in boiling water bath 15 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 pints.

title: prune nut cupcakes
directions: Combine as you do a cake.
Bake in small cupcake pans at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
The number of cupcakes this recipe makes depends on the size of your pans.

title: montego bay bars
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Cook dates, sugar, water and chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly about 10 minutes or until mixture thickens; cool.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour in pan.
Bake until done. Cut into squares.

title: mashed rutabagas and carrots
directions: Scrape carrots and peel off wax surface from rutabagas.
Cut rutabagas into 1/4-inch chunks and cut carrots into 1/2-inch pieces.
Drop into boiling pot of water and cook until vegetables are soft.
Drain pot and mash all the ingredients, adding the black pepper and onion powder.
Serve in a bowl (like mashed potatoes) with butter.

title: giant gingerbread kids
directions: Beat sugar, shortening, molasses and water in large bowl. Beat on low speed of mixer until blended.
Beat on medium speed 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients except raisins.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled, 1 to 2 hours.
Heat oven to 375°. Sprinkle a cloth-covered surface lightly with flour; turn dough onto
surface.
Roll dough with a rolling pin until 1/4-inch thick. Cut with a 5 to 8-inch gingerbread cutter.
Lift with large spatula onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate with raisins. Bake until set, 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cookies cool 3 minutes, then remove.
Cool and decorate with frosting, if you like.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with vegetable dippers.
Makes 4 cups.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix eggs, oleo, milk, soda, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Add flour.
Roll thin and cut out shapes.
Bake at 350° for approximately 5 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Thinly slice zucchini and line the bottom of a 1 1/2-quart pan. Add enough grated Mozzarella cheese to cover or to your liking. Sprinkle on 1/2 of the browned sausage and repeat layer once more. Place in oven at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Makes a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: buret of lemon whipped cream
directions: Combine cream and pie filling mix in mixer bowl.
Whip until thickened.
Serve on fresh fruit, short cake, gingerbread or other desserts.
Makes 2 cups.

title: banana butternut ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 4-quart ice cream churn.

title: throw-together beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on high for 3 or 4 hours or on low for 6 hours.

title: cake filling
directions: Mix vanilla pudding and pineapple.
Fold in Dream Whip.
For white, lemon or yellow cake.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Add sugar a little at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix and add morsels and pecans.
Set oven at 350°.
Drop on ungreased pan.
Shut off oven when you put the cookies in and leave overnight.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook chicken and chop up.
Save broth and cook spaghetti, celery and onions in broth until tender.
Add soup and half of cheese; mix and pour in casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cut up cabbage.
Fry bacon and drain. Crumble up bacon.
Put into pan with cabbage.
Simmer until tender. Sprinkle with Accent and soy sauce to taste.

title: phil's chili
directions: Soak kidney and navy beans in 3 cups of water overnight in refrigerator.
Heat an 8-quart heavy pan.
Add the oil (or spray the bottom); saute bean flakes for 5 minutes on low heat (do not brown).
Add 4 cups of heated water and rice.
Drain water from beans, add to saucepan and continue to simmer, uncovered, on low heat.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown meat, butter and onion in skillet.
In 5-quart container, prepare and mix together remaining ingredients.
Stir in browned meat mixture and simmer for 1 hour.
(Tastes the best next day.)

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except whole pecans; sprinkle whole pecans evenly in bottom of greased baking pan.
Pour into pan and bake 50 minutes in oven at 350°.
Use 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Simmer eggplant in a little water for a few minutes; drain well.
Combine with other ingredients except 1/4 cup crumbs and margarine.
Pour into greased casserole (2-quart).
Top with 1/4 cup crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and browned, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Can be flavored with grated onion, if desired.

title: swiss bliss
directions: Spread 20-inch sheet of heavy foil in pan.
Add steak pieces. Sprinkle onion soup, mushrooms and green pepper.
Mix juice, A.1. sauce and cornstarch.
Pour over meat.
Close foil tightly and bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Garnish with parsley.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Slice strawberries into 2 baked pie shells.
In medium saucepan, combine cornstarch and water and cook until thick.
Add 1 package dry strawberry jello.
Pour liquid over strawberries. Refrigerate until jelled.
Spoon Cool Whip over and serve.
Keep refrigerated.

title: radish cream cheese dip
directions: Mix together all but vegetables until smooth. Stir in veggies and chill several hours.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream margarine, brown sugar, and eggs.
Mix thoroughly. Sift together and add to mixture flour, soda, and cinnamon.
Add milk and flavoring.
Mix and add chopped fruit and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon into well greased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 20-30 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix sausage, onion, rice, cheese and chopped tomatoes together.
Scald the cabbage leaves and roll the meat mixture in the leaves.
Put the canned tomatoes over the cabbage rolls.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and pour in a casserole dish bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Take out of oven and top with last 3 ingredients mixed together and bake for 10
to 14 more minutes

title: barbecued chicken bake
directions: Prepare chicken as to fry.
Do not flavor.
Place in a baking pan, skin side down.
Salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.
Pour off juice and turn pieces.
Pour sauce over and bake 40 minutes or until done.

title: lime pickles
directions: Take cucumbers and cover with water and lime and let stand for 24 hours.
Rinse well and let stand in clear water for 3 hours. Drain well.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Mix rice with dry onion soup, cream of chicken soup and water. Brown chicken and lay in pan on the soup mixture.
Put in the oven, uncovered, and cook for 1 to 2 hours at 350°, until done.

title: barbecued beef 'n pork
directions: Place both roasts in roaster; cook in a 325° oven for 3 to 4 hours, or until meat falls apart.
Make gravy out of drippings. Add your favorite barbecue sauce.
Add the beef and pork to it. Serve on buns.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth.
When done, put chicken, rice, string beans and cut up water chestnuts in large skillet and simmer for one hour (adding more broth, if necessary).

title: dilly cauliflower and peas
directions: Cook cauliflower according to package directions.
In medium saucepan, saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons margarine until tender.
Add cauliflower, peas, dill weed and salt; heat through.

title: cream pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, salt and milk
until thick, then add the beaten egg yolks.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Put ingredients in a large bowl; mix together with hands. Spread in to an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Pat down, cut in squares and refrigerate.

title: coconut dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix with 1 cup milk as directed on package, using large mixer bowl. Add remaining milk and the pudding mix. Blend, then beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Fold in coconut. Spoon into crust. Chill until serving time.

title: zesty italian chicken
directions: Place chicken in a medium size bowl and pour the large bottle of dressing over the chicken.
Marinate overnight or at least 2 hours before cooking.

title: chicken breasts carla
directions: Place chicken breasts between sheets of plastic wrap.
Pound slightly with mallet, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil and butter in large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 2 minutes on each side.
Do not overcook!
Transfer to warm serving platter.
Add green onions and lemon juice, parsley and mustard to skillet and cook 15 seconds, stirring constantly.
Stir in broth.
Stir until smooth.
Add remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve immediately.

title: krumkaka
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually, beating until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in cardamom.
Sift flour and salt together.
Blend into egg mixture alternately with cream.
Place 1 tablespoon batter a little off center on krumkaka iron.
Close lid and cook a few minutes, turning the pan once to brown both sides. Remove from iron with spatula and roll immediately into cone shape.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except corn flakes and butter. Put in a baking dish and top with mixture of corn flakes and butter. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: orange-cheese salad(lite)
directions: Mix orange jello with Cool Whip.
Add cheese, oranges, pineapple and coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: quick salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon.
In mixing bowl, combine salmon, egg and onion; stir in flour and corn meal.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Form in small patties.
Fry in hot shortening until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add brown sugar; stir until smooth.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Serve at room temperature as a dip with fresh fruits. Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: broccoli or spinach - your choice - casserole
directions: In a bowl, mix well cream cheese, milk, softened butter, and marinade (from jar of artichoke hearts).
Place both sets of artichoke hearts in bottom
of oven baking dish or casserole. Spread chopped cooked broccoli or cooked spinach over artichokes. Sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
I also season with pepper, paprika and 1 teaspoon of tarragon.
This originally came from Alaska.
It's easy to do! Enjoy!
Serves 6 to 8.

title: canned tomato juice
directions: Fill a 5-gallon bucket full of red ripe tomatoes.
In two 8-quart pans quarter the tomatoes.
Cook until mushy; then strain through colander.
Put in large pan.
Add a sprinkle of oregano, garlic, pepper and 1/2 sprinkle of basil.
Add sugar, salt and bay leaf.
Heat to nearly boiling.
Place in quart mason jars and pressure cook for 10 minutes at 5 pounds PSI.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add buttermilk, sugar and shortening.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Roll out dough; cut or shape as desired.
Place on greased pan.
Let rise in warm place for 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 2 dozen rolls.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except egg whites.
Beat egg white and fold into batter mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open oven.

title: chalupas
directions: Heat oil in skillet (1/8 inch) over medium heat until hot. Place tortillas, one at a time, in hot oil, bending one side up about 1 inch with tongs until set.
Repeat with other side to form a shallow boat.
Mix beans, chili powder, garlic powder and oregano.
Spread about 1/4 cup on each tortilla; top with cheese. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Heat oven to broil; place cookie sheet under for 2 to 3 minutes until cheese has melted.
Serve with tomato and avocado wedges and salsa.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over chicken that has been fried brown.
Put in oven and slowly bake in a 275° oven for 1 hour.

title: cheese ham fondue
directions: In a 2-quart casserole (glass, 8 1/4 x 3/4-inch round), layer the bread,	ham
and cheese.
Layer the remaining bread, ham, cheese.
In a small bowl stir together flour and mustard. Gradually stir in
milk,
keep
smooth.
In
medium bowl, beat eggs slightly; add	milk and Tabasco, blend.
Pour over ingredients in casserole.
Bake
at
until
browned and knife inserted comes out
clean, about 45 minutes.	Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: *You can use regular flour plus 2 tsp. of baking powder and 1 tsp. salt.

title: nancy's chili
directions: Brown meats and onion.
Add chillo mix and all ingredients, except jalapenos.
Simmer.
Add jalapenos before serving.

title: raised waffles
directions: Stir first 2 ingredients and let stand 5 minutes.
Add next 5 ingredients and beat until smooth.
Place in covered dish and let stand outside of refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, add 2 eggs and a pinch of soda.
Beat well with spoon or beater.
Batter will look thin.
Makes 6 waffles.
These freeze well.

title: diabetic pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, fructose, evaporated milk and eggs in large bowl.
Beat to blend.
Blend cornstarch in cold water and beat into pumpkin mixture.
Beat in cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and ginger. Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread into greased casserole dish. Cover with corn flakes and butter mixture.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: butterscotch muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine the flour, sugar and pudding mixes. Combine the water, eggs, oil and vanilla. Stir into
dry ingredients just until moistened. Fill greased muffin cups two-thirds full. Combine the brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon and sprinkle over batter. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cool and take meat from bones; put in small pieces.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup and milk together.
Pour over chicken breast pieces.
Fix 1 box Stove Top dressing as directed on box.
Spoon over chicken and soup mixture.
Bake until heated thoroughly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and water and cook until clear.
Then add jello and stir until dissolved.
Cool and add strawberries.
Pour into cold cooked pie shell.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: rich chocolate cake
directions: Note:
I sift flour and cocoa together.

title: sourdough pancakes(made from sourdough batter)
directions: Remove 1 cup starter batter to hold over in refrigerator.
To remaining batter, add egg, shortening and milk.
Beat well. Combine salt, soda and sugar.
Blend into batter.
Allow to sit a few minutes, then fry on hot griddle.
If necessary, add a bit more flour to make the right consistency.

title: chicken balls
directions: Blend well.
Shape into balls. Roll into nuts and chill.

title: custard
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, nutmeg, salt and vanilla.
Pour into the hot milk,
Blend together with mixer.
Beat real good, then refrigerate.

title: favorite carrot cake
directions: Sift cinnamon, nutmeg, soda and salt into batter. (I sift with flour.) Add pecans. Beat.

title: white mountain salad
directions: Whip cream, add sugar.
Mix with cottage cheese.
Add marshmallows, cherries and pineapple.
Chill.
Serve as a salad or dessert.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crumble 2 sleeves of crackers in bottom of large casserole dish with 3/4 stick of butter or margarine, melted.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter together. Stir in honey graham cereal.
Pour powdered sugar in a plastic bag or bowl, add mixed ingredients and shake well until all coated. Pour out on foil or wax paper to cool.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Saute onions and bell pepper, oil and shredded ham.
Combine potatoes, butter, salt, pepper and sour cream; mix well.
Blend in bacon, ham and 1 cup cheese.
Spoon into potato shells.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until cheese is bubbly.

title: cream cheese pound cake 2
directions: Cream butter, margarine and cream cheese with sugar. Add eggs one at a time. Mix well. Add flavorings. Mix again. Pour into a greased cake pan and bake at 250° for 1 hr. and 45 minutes.

title: home made buns
directions: Measure flour, put 6 cups in pan to mix with remaining ingredients.
Mix the other 6 cups of flour 1/2 cup at a time until all flour is mixed in.
The dough will be soft.
Do not use any more flour than what is called for.
Grease sides and bottom of pan and knead the dough for about 5 minutes.
Let rise to double it's size.
Mix down and let rise again.
Make into buns, let rise to double their size and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion in oleo and combine with eggs.
Add soup, squash, bread crumbs, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot mulled apple juice
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Remove spices; serve warm.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine or butter and sugar; add egg yolk, flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Roll pieces of dough into small balls, about the size of a marble.
Press down with prongs of a fork which has been dipped into flour.
Brush top with unbeaten egg white.
May top with bit of candied cherry or walnut.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 20 minutes or until firm.

title: grandma's walnut pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine eggs, sugar, flour, syrup, butter and vanilla; blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Arrange walnuts on top.
Bake in lower third of oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°; bake an additional 35 to 45 minutes or until center appears set.
Cool completely. Yields 8 servings.

title: girl scout punch
directions: Mix ingredients together. Chill and serve.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: With a brush, scrub cucumbers under cold running water; drain. Do not peel, but trim ends. Slice thin.
There should be 8 cups. Peel onion, quarter and slice thin.
There should be 1 cup. Quarter green pepper, remove seeds and membrane; rinse.
Slice thin crosswise.
There should be 1 cup.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix beaten egg yolks, sugar, flour, milk and butter or margarine in top of double boiler.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Cool.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Cover with meringue made from stiffly beaten egg whites and 10 tablespoons sugar.
Brown at 350°.

title: festive frozen mint pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk, peppermint extract and food coloring.
Fold in whipped cream.
Turn into crust. Cover. Freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Garnish as desired. Freeze leftovers.

title: lasagne
directions: In a large pan, lightly brown beef and onion in oil. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar and spices. Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally until sauce is thick and not watery.
Cook lasagne noodles and drain.

title: broiled shad(fish and oysters)
directions: When the fish is cleaned, wash, wipe and split it.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Lay it upon a buttered gridiron, inside down.
When the lower side is done, turn the fish.
One of medium size will take 20 minutes.
Serve hot, lay a good piece of butter on the fish.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar well; add the eggs and beat. Sift flour, soda, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add nuts and apples; mix lightly.
Press into approximately 7 x 11 x 1 1/2-inch pan rubbed with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook or thaw frozen spinach.
Rinse, drain and squeeze out excess liquid.
Combine all the ingredients in a medium size bowl. Mix thoroughly.
Chill for 3 hours.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Blend Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar well. Spread into pie crust. Arrange peaches on top and cover with glaze. Chill before serving.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 or 10.

title: rick's coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar, flour and eggs together.
Add milk, butter, vanilla and coconut (melt butter).
Mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 375° until set and brown (approximately 40 to 45 minutes) on center shelf in oven.
Yields 2 pies.

title: marinated oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let marinate for a couple of days before serving. Crackers will stay crisp for days if they are stored in airtight container. Yield: 4 cups.

title: crow's nest(apple dessert)
directions: Peel apples; slice and put in deep dish pie plate.
Put biscuit mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until apples are done.
Invert dough onto plate; remove apples and mix apples with white sugar, brown sugar and nutmeg.
Put apple mixture back on top of biscuit top.
This is a very old recipe.

title: orange pecans
directions: Bring orange juice, orange rind and sugar to a boil in a heavy saucepan.
Stir in pecans and continue to cook.
Stir until all syrup is absorbed.
Remove from heat.
Spread out on wax paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: meat casserole
directions: Add garlic salt and pepper to hamburger meat and brown.
Rinse and drain meat in a colander to reduce fat content.
Add tomato sauce and stewed tomatoes.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
In a bowl, blend cream cheese and sour cream.
Set aside.

title: hearty pizza
directions: Prepare hot roll mix as directed and place in greased bowl to rise.
Meanwhile, make Italian sauce; saute the onion in 1 tablespoon oil until golden.
Add the tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt, oregano, garlic salt and pepper.
Heat sauce.
Spread dough on large pizza pan (15 x 10-inch or equivalent circle).
Lay the Mozzarella cheese on dough and cover with sauce.
Bake at 425° for 13 to 18 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: 8 minute cheesecake
directions: Beat the cheese until smooth.
Gradually add sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip, mixing well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill at least 4 hours.
May be garnished with your favorite pie filling.

title: garry dogs
directions: Chop wieners into 1/2-inch thick pieces.
Cut cheese into 1-inch squares.
Mix other ingredients into bowl.
Spoon into hot dog buns.
Wrap each bun in foil.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: robert's baste and dab-on sauce
directions: In a large boiler, bring to boil the first 9 ingredients, stirring enough to prevent boiling over.
Reduce heat and simmer 12-15 minutes with lid on.
Rinse mop in hot water.
Use mop to dab and baste meat while it cooks on the grill.
Dab and baste every few minutes until meat is done to your liking.
Just before removing from grill, add you favorite barbecue sauce to meat. This is a good baste and dab sauce for chicken halves, pork ribs, Boston butt, country cut backbone or steak.
This is a little salty, but the salt draws the grease out of the meat.
Also good as a marinade.
Pour any leftover into a jar and refrigerate.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all above ingredients together well and chill overnight.

title: ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Cream butter, Worcestershire sauce, celery seed and mustard together.
Finely chop the ham and add it and the shredded cheese to mixture.
Mix well with spoon and generously spoon mixture on hamburger buns.
Sandwiches may be heated individually by wrapping sandwich in paper towel and microwave it for 30 seconds.
To fix several sandwiches at once, you may also wrap them in foil and bake them in oven on 275° for 30 minutes.
Refrigerate unused mixture.

title: split pea and ham soup
directions: In large pot, combine oil, onions and garlic and cook until onions are tender.
Add all remaining ingredients except salt. Boil, then lower heat and cook 90 minutes.
Remove meat and bone. Skim fat.
Cut up meat and return to soup.
Discard bay leaves. Stir well before serving.

title: gloria's chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until boiling.
Cook until firm ball stage (a drop of mixture dropped in cold water will form a firm ball).
Stir constantly. After ball stage, add last 2 ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Grease an 8 x 11-inch pan and pour in. Spread evenly.
Let set until firm.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Beat the first 7 ingredients at high speed for 2 minutes.
Add the nuts to the mixture.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or oblong pan at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Frost cake if desired when cooled with favorite frosting or store bought frosting.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour mixture, 3 or 4 tablespoons at a time, alternating with milk, ending with flour.
Grease pan lined with waxed or brown paper. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: apple-cranberry brew
directions: Proportions are for a 10-cup percolator.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Combine the package of beef Rice-A-Roni with the ground beef and the beaten egg.
Shape into small balls (approximately 20); brown on all sides.
Combine contents of beef seasoning packet with the hot water; pour over meat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Thicken gravy, if desired.

title: shrimp corn soup
directions: Make 1 tablespoon of roux.
After brown, add onions and shrimp.
Smother down and add all other ingredients.
Cook for 1 hour and serve.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, oleo, milk and cocoa in 3 quart pan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until mixed well.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper to cool.
Makes about 3 dozen small cookies.

title: low fat fritters
directions: Mix first three ingredients. Add enough skim milk to make the consistency of cake batter. Spray non stick skillet with Pam and heat. Pour about 3/4 cup batter in skillet and brown on both sides. Serve with your favorite toppings. I use peanut butter and syrup.

title: moist and easy chicken
directions: Mix mayonnaise, mustard and horseradish together; brush it on chicken on all sides.
Place bread crumbs in large plastic bag. Add chicken, one piece at a time; shake well to coat.
Place on broiler rack in broiler pan; bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Blend oleo, peanut butter and both sugars.
Add egg and stir in dry ingredients.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place in ungreased tasse pans.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Unwrap peanut butter cups.
Remove cups from oven and place a Reese's cup in each warm ball.
Let set a few minutes. Remove from pan.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: quick beef dish
directions: Brown meat; remove from pan and saute pepper and onion in drippings.
Pour meat, onion, pepper, soup and milk in 2-quart baking dish; place biscuits on top, covering mixture completely with biscuits.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are golden brown.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Cook the chicken until it falls apart easily.
Drain any water or excess liquids from chicken.
Add the salsa to the chicken and simmer about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: hello dolly cookies
