directions: Melt butter in baking pan (9 x 13-inch) and spread.
Layer bottom of pan with graham cracker crumbs.
Layer with chocolate chips (save some for topping).
Layer with coconut and pecans. Sprinkle top with chocolate chips.
Drizzle Eagle Brand milk on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
It will loosen around edges. Remove from oven.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all and form into flattened ball.
Pour cocktail sauce over before serving.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine crumbs, butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Work together until smooth.
Press firmly into 9-inch square buttered pan.
Melt chocolate and spread on top.
Refrigerate until firm and cut into squares.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together over low heat.
Beat 3 eggs.
Add the flour, sugar, vanilla and salt to the eggs. Gradually add the melted chocolate and butter mixture.
After the mixture is well beaten, pour into the pie shell and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: Mix sugar and Karo syrup in saucepan; boil until it spins a thread. Add butter, small pieces at a time, then warmed cream.
Boil until it reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and let cool 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and salt.
Pour over popped corn and shape into balls.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels in a double boiler with cream.
Mix flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, soda, butter and salt until crumbly.
Put half of crumbly mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Put on chocolate chips, nuts (optional) and caramel mixture.
Spread rest of dry mixture over the top.
Bake 15 minutes more at 350°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and beat well until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Mix in flour well and add vanilla. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 30 minutes.

title: english bread pudding
directions: Break bread into small pieces; place in deep bowl. Pour milk over bread; mix well. Cover and let sit for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low heat.
Combine sugar, eggs, flour, milk and vanilla; stir well.
Gradually add chocolate mixture, stirring constantly.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Put Cool Whip on each piece.

title: chicken divan
directions: Simmer chicken breasts for 1/2 hour in water or chicken broth; cool.
Thaw broccoli completely.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place broccoli in pan.
Cut chicken breasts in half; put each chicken breast so it covers the broccoli.
Mix sherry, mayo and soup; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate cake frosting
directions: Blend in heavy saucepan.
Boil over light heat 3 minutes while stirring.
Reduce heat and cook until it reaches soft ball stage. Cool and beat until creamy.
Spread on 2 layer cake.

title: jalapeno cheese squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cheese and pepper, then press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend eggs, flour and milk well and pour over cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.
Good for parties.

title: easy, easy quiche
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Place cheese in pans.
Cover with bacon and onion.
In blender, mix milk, eggs, salt, pepper and flour and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° until center is set.
Each quiche will serve 4 to 6.
Pie shells may be fit into a 9 x 13-inch pan, pinching together, and baked in that manner.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir halfway of cooking time.

title: canandian honey drops
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in honey and vanilla.
Measure flour by dip-level-pour method or by sifting.
Blend flour and soda; stir in.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Cook sugar, flour, egg and pineapple juice until thick.
Cool completely. Add pineapple, marshmallows and cheese. I put grated cheese on top, too.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Brown onions in oil.
Add water, ketchup, Worcestershire, vinegar, lemon juice, salt, pepper and Texas Pete.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add chicken pieces and cook on low heat until tender. Can be cooked in oven in 9 x 13-inch baking dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy chicken and spaghetti
directions: Heat on low for 20 minutes.
Add deboned chicken.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth, add water if needed.
Drain spaghetti and place on platter.
Pour chicken sauce over it and serve.
Top with Parmesan Cheese.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together first 6 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes approximately 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: punch for a bunch
directions: Combine all ingredients. Begin adding water and sugar (approximately 2 1/2 pounds) to make up 4 gallons of punch.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Simmer chicken breasts in water (just to cover) with carrot, celery tops and salt until tender, about 45 minutes.
Strain broth.
Save vegetables and 1 cup broth.
Debone, skin and dice chicken.
Mix 1/4 cup butter and 1/2 of broth with 1 package of dressing mix.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix vegetables, chicken, 1/2 cup broth, sour cream and soup.
Spread over dressing in pan.
Mix other box of dressing with 1/4 cup butter and 1/2 cup broth.
Spread over other mixture.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherry cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, eggs, oil and extract.
Add the pie filling. Mix well.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream date pie
directions: Combine sour cream, egg, brown sugar, dates, walnuts, lemon rind and salt.
Mix well.
Pour filling into unbaked pie shell. Cover with lattice top and flute edge.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 10 minutes and then reduce temperature to slow oven to 325°. Bake until filling is set and crust lightly browned.
Takes about 30 minutes.
Serve with sweetened whipped cream.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: broccoli dip appetizer
directions: Saute celery and onion in a small amount of butter or margarine.
Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Mix all together using a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and put in microwave until cheese melts, stirring every few minutes to prevent burning.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: toffee candy
directions: In a heavy saucepan melt butter and sugar.
Stir constantly until candy thermometer reaches 290° (watch carefully to prevent scorching).
Remove from heat; add soda and stir.
Pour in a thin ribbon quickly over 2 cookie sheets.
Immediately top with Hershey bars, they soften and can be spread with a spatula.
Cool and chocolate hardens.
Break into pieces.
Store in an airtight container.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Spray a 15 x 10-inch pan with Pam.
At medium speed of electric mixer, mix together the flour, butter (cut in pieces), sugar and salt.
Press the dough of this mixture into the pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 23 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes; dissolve in boiling water.
In a large saucepan, simmer all other ingredients except lemon juice for 15 minutes.
Strain; add lemon juice and dissolved gelatin.
Turn into a large 10-inch ring mold or 6 individual molds; chill until set.
(To fill a larger mold, double the recipe but use 5 tablespoons gelatin instead of 4.)

title: baked chicken
directions: Combine the chicken, rice, celery and pimientos. Add the salt, poultry seasoning, baking powder, eggs, and broth. Put in casserole. Cover with crumbs, dot with butter. Bake 55 min. at 350°.

title: chicken-broccoli bake
directions: Cut chicken into generous chunks.
Spray Mazola in a large casserole dish.
Melt margarine and mix stuffing, stirring well. Sprinkle 1/3 of stuffing mixture on bottom of dish.
Add 1/2 of the chicken and 1 package of broccoli.
Spread 1/2 of the soup mix over chicken and broccoli, then layer the crumbs.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes alot; great for company.

title: cocoa-chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in mini chips.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Sprinkle salt on shredded cabbage; let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out liquid from cabbage.
Mix together celery and cabbage.
Combine vinegar, salt, water, sugar and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute.
Let cool.
Pour over cabbage mixture and mix well.
Freeze in containers.
When ready to use, thaw in refrigerator, pour off juice and squeeze out liquid.
Mix with mayonnaise or your favorite dressing.
Shredded carrots, onions or peppers can be added.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: After you cook pudding, let cool about 5 minutes, then pour in cake mix and oil and stir well.
Pour into greased cake pan and top with 1 small package of chocolate chips and 1 cup pecans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb celery salad
directions: Make gelatin according to directions on package.
When gelatin is syrupy, stir in drained rhubarb sauce and chopped celery. Chill until firm.
Serve with salad dressing.
Serves 6.

title: amish pie crust
directions: Mix till coarse crumbs.
Very easy to handle. Enough for 2 - 9 inch crusts.

title: rasmussen's deer salami
directions: Mix well. Refrigerate for 3 days (each day, mix well).
On the fourth day, divide and roll into balls.
Place on broiler pan or wire rack on cookie sheet. Cure in warm oven no higher than 200° for 8 hours (turn after 4 hours).
Refrigerate up to 3 weeks or freeze up to 2 months.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook everything except chicken and bread crumbs until thick. Make 2 layers of each in 9 x 13 pan.
Chicken on the bottom, then mixture.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Cook 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: smoky mountain barbecued ribs(serves 20)
directions: Cover ribs with water.
Add salt and simmer 45 minutes.
Cool ribs in liquid.
Drain and save liquid for sauce.
Combine flour, paprika, chili powder, pepper and mustard.
Roll cooled ribs in mixture to coat.
Place in roasting pan at an angle.
Cover with onion and lemon slices.
Pour Mountain Cabin Barbecue Sauce over and bake.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt; and add to sugar mixture.
Chill.
Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Remove dough from refrigerator and roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in the sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, butter and salt in large saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat (a hard rolling boil) and boil 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla; blend well.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper or pour into a greased jelly roll pan and cut into squares when cool.

title: peach sherbet
directions: Use a gallon size ice cream freezer.

title: every good cook's chicken stock
directions: Select a stockpot large enough to comfortably hold the above ingredients.
Place the chicken, veal knuckle and water in pot; bring to a boil.
Skim foam; add all the other ingredients.
Bring back to a boil; reduce to the lowest possible heat.
You want this to be barely simmering.
Continue cooking for about 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally as necessary.
Strain the cooked stock through a damp cheesecloth lined colander; discard all solids. Cool and refrigerate the stock.
When fat has congealed on top, remove and discard it.
The stock may be used as is or frozen. Makes 3 1/2 to 4 quarts.

title: orange juice popsicles
directions: Beat dry milk and water until stiff.
Mix with remaining ingredients and freeze.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Beat margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks, two at a time.
Beat well.
Add flour and soda alternately with buttermilk. Add coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites (fold in).
Pour in 2 well-greased cake pans.
Bake at 350°.

title: poor boy rolls
directions: Heat oil.
Mix milk and flour until it pulls off sides of bowl.
Spoon off into hot oil.
Turn over with slotted spoon until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.

title: norske vafler(waffles)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Let batter rest at least 30 minutes.
Use more or less flour depending on desired thickness. Serve these cold with cranberries stirred in sugar and vanilla sugar and whipped sour cream.

title: cheesy carapple dessert
directions: Roll out biscuits to fit long cookie sheet.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar.
Spread over dough.
Spread apples over top.
Sprinkle over top of dough the chopped nuts.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
This dessert is not real sweet, but it is delicious.

title: chunky pretzels
directions: Break pretzels into pieces.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour oil over and stir.
Mix remaining ingredients together and add to pretzels.
Mix well.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Cool and store in a plastic bag.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Put hamburger in large pan or skillet.
Cook until brown on medium-high.
Salt.
Add sauce mix, tomato paste, water and mushrooms to hamburger.
Reduce heat to low.
Add margarine. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Cook 1 pound of spaghetti.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, just enough to blend.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or microwave for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O into Cool Whip. Add remaining ingredients. Stir well and refrigerate.

title: individual cheesecakes
directions: You will need 24 foil mini cupcake liners.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar, flour and milk in top of double boiler.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.

title: chicken deluxe
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Pierce with fork; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Arrange with thicker portions toward outside in 8 x 12-inch glass dish.
Cover with vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 8 to 9 minutes or until thickest portion is no longer pink, rotating dish 1/4 turn after 4 minutes.
Let stand, covered with foil, for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine soup, sour cream, onion and parsley flakes in 4-cup glass measure.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all together and store in airtight jar.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons in mug of boiling water.
Enjoy!

title: eggplant appetizer
directions: Wash eggplant; cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
In 1/2 cup hot oil in
large skillet, saute eggplant until tender and golden brown. Remove eggplant and set aside.

title: chipped ham barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onions in shortening until soft, not brown.
Add remaining ingredients, except ham.
Mix thoroughly.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add ham and heat. Serve on buns.

title: marinade for steak
directions: Pour over meat.
I prefer a London broil.
Cover and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours, turning occasionally.
Grill as preferred, basting occasionally.

title: applesauce frenchies
directions: Mix 2 cups (one 1 pound jar) applesauce, butter, cinnamon and nutmeg and heat.
Beat eggs and milk with a dash of salt.
Dip 8 slices of bread into this mixture and brown on both sides in hot butter or margarine.
Place applesauce mixture between 2 slices of toasted bread and on top.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy mexican dip
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add salsa and velveeta cheese to hamburger and heat till cheese melts.
Place in crock pot on low to keep warm.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or fritos.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Make cake according to package directions;
adding the butter.
Add poppy seeds during last minute of beating.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix flour, 1/4 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon cocoa and oil in an 8 x 8-inch square pan.	Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa and sprinkle over
mixture.
Pour
water
on top of mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake
at
for	20
to	30
minutes. Delicious served with ice cream or whipped cream.
Middle will be like pudding.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients; blend in Crisco.
Take orange juice and add enough water to make 3/4 cup liquid; add. Add egg; mix together.
Fold in cranberries and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Can be cooked on top of stove in cast-iron skillet.
Mix all ingredients (except cheese) and bring to a boil; reduce heat to simmer (low).
Cover and cook for approximately 30 minutes.
Cover with cheese the last 5 minutes of cooking time or add all ingredients (except cheese) in casserole pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour, covering with cheese the last 5 minutes of cooking time.

title: brownie mix
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cocoa, then cut in shortening until evenly distributed.
Mixture can be stored up to 12 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: forgotten beef roast
directions: Put meat in roasting pan.
Cut potatoes, carrots and mushrooms in chunks and place around meat.
Spoon cream of mushroom soup on top.
Seal pan tight with aluminum foil.
Bake at 300° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: white icing
directions: Mix ingredients; beat 5 minutes.

title: mac-nuggets
directions: Marinate the chicken pieces in mixture of the other ingredients for at least 2 hours.

title: sausage and potato au gratin
directions: In crock-pot, add enough water to cover bottom.
Slice half the potatoes and place in crock.
Slice half the sauce and add to crock.
Add half the cheese.
Add additional layer of potatoes, sausage and cheese.
Spoon cream of mushroom or chicken soup over the top and sprinkle with paprika.
Cook on low setting all day.

title: chocolate ice cream(tastes like wendy's frosty)
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Follow directions pertaining to your ice cream freezer for the exact amount of time required to freeze.

title: spicy grilled chicken
directions: Cut breasts in half.
In a shallow bowl, combine oil, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, hot pepper sauce and salt and pepper.
Coat chicken with mixture.
Grill or broil 6 to 8-inches away from heat for 10 to 20 minutes.
Turn 2 to 3 times.

title: frichick helper(quick and easy)
directions: Follow directions for Tuna Helper only substitute the Frichick for the tuna.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix meatball ingredients.
Shape into twenty 1 1/2-inch balls. Cook over medium heat, turning occasionally, until brown, about 20 minutes.
Can cook in oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) in 400° oven until light brown, about 20 minutes.
Drain off fat.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger. Add chopped onion. Cook thoroughly. Drain and add taco seasoning and 1/4 cup of water. Simmer 5 minutes. Add the tomato sauce. Stir thoroughly. Add chips (better if you mash them a little). Mix until chips are covered. Put in casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese and place in the oven for 15 minutes or until the cheese is melted.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add cocoa, flour and sugar.
Mix well and add milk. Cook on medium heat until thickens.
Serve over hot buttered biscuits.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute frozen mixed veggies in oil and 2 Tbsp. of soy sauce. Cover with lid.
Saute until tender.
Combine cooked rice and veggies with 1 package of the fried rice seasoning and 1/2 cup soy sauce.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add extra soy sauce if desired.

title: bird's nest
directions: Mix ingredients; chill thoroughly.
Roll in small balls.
Dip first in slightly beaten egg white, then in finely chopped nuts. Place dipped side up on baking sheet.
Press down in the center of each ball with a spoon to make a hollow place or make a thumbprint.
Bake for 8 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken jamaica
directions: Place pineapple rings in bottom of pan.
Lay chicken breasts on the pineapple.
Cover chicken with soup.
Place 1 teaspoon of instant coffee on each chicken breast.
Bake 1 hour in a 350 degree oven.
Sprinkle cheddar cheese (optional) over chicken and melt before removing from oven.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix first four items and boil.
Microwave does it nicely. Arrange chicken pieces in baking dish.
Pour sauce over.
Bake one hour at 375° uncovered.
Halfway through, turn chicken and baste with sauce.

title: red ball chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Cover bottom of baking dish (casserole) with beef jerky.
Wrap a slice of bacon around each chicken breast and place on top of jerky.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over top, making sure you cover chicken.
Bake for 3 to 3 1/2 hours and serve with rice.

title: little cheese cakes
directions: Mix above.
Put in miniature pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip topping.

title: crab and shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix well and serve with crackers.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix
sugar
and
flour; set aside.
Mix oleo, cocoa and Coca-Cola.
Bring
to a boil.
Add to flour and sugar mixture. Mix together buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Add to first mixture,
mix
well.
Bake
in
greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pear relish
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a large sauce pan.
Bring mixture to a boil and reduce the heat.
Simmer for 45 minutes stirring frequently.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars and seal yields: 8 to 9.

title: summer squash soup
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil. Cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes. Add carrots and simmer 8 to 10 minutes more until carrots and potatoes are tender. Add rest of ingredients and stir. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes more.
Remove cover and cool.
Whirl in food processor. Add 2 tablespoons chopped fresh basil or 2 teaspoons dry.

title: chocolate walnut sensations
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Set aside.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Remove from heat and gradually blend in milk.
Set aside.

title: window cleaner
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into spray bottle.

title: snow peas and water chestnuts
directions: Fry the pork in hot oil in preheated skillet; add the peas, water chestnuts and monosodium glutamate, then add the broth. Steam, covered, over high heat about 3 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and cold water; push vegetables to one side and add cornstarch mixture to broth; cook and stir until slightly thick. Add salt to taste.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together like for cake mix.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cooled, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sausage cheese bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and butter (with mixer) until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat until creamy. Alternate flour and milk beginning with flour and ending with flour. Add salt and lemon extract. Bake in tube pan, greased and floured, at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Check after 1 hour. Ovens vary. Cool in pan for 15 minutes. Turn out on cake plate.

title: lane cake
directions: Follow directions on box for a 2 (9-inch) layer cake.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly. Combine dry ingredients and add to first mixture followed by nuts, vanilla and milk.
Form into two 2-inch rolls and wrap in waxed paper.
Refrigerate until firm.
Slice thin and bake on ungreased cookie sheets in 350° oven until brown.
Remove directly from sheets.
Cool completely before storing in airtight containers.

title: tomato sauce
directions: In medium bowl mix well all ingredients.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: cranberry nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper liners.

title: fruity chicken salad
directions: Stew chicken breasts until done. Remove from water and sprinkle with celery salt. Cool and cut into bite-size pieces. Add the pineapple, nuts, grapes and mayonnaise. Mix together adding more mayonnaise as needed. Then, gently fold in the mandarin oranges. Chill before serving.

title: chocolate butterscotch cake
directions: *Bake German chocolate cake according to directions for a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: banana split cake i
directions: You will also need one 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Line baking pan with tinfoil.
Place in chicken.
Heat ingredients together so that they're mixed well.
Pour sauce over chicken. Cover and bake 1 hour, then uncovered for 15 minutes at 350°.
Excellent served with wild rice.

title: mrs. bowie's custard pie
directions: Mix sugar with melted margarine.
Add eggs, beaten well. Next, add flour and salt, then add milk and flavoring.
Bake in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell at 350° for at least 30 minutes.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Dissolve lime gelatin in 1 cup hot water. Add marshmallows, stirring until nearly dissolved; remove from heat. Add the crushed pineapple, including juice. Blend together the mayonnaise and cream cheese. Add to first mixture. Chill until slightly set. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into flat pan. Chill until firm. Dissolve in 2 cups hot water the cherry gelatin. Cool but do not jell. Pour over first mixture. Chill until set.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients about 10 minutes.
Add the margarine.
Add the flour.
Add the milk.
Cook until thickened. Add the cheese.
Drain some liquid from the broccoli before adding to milk mixture.
If needed, add broccoli liquid and/or milk to make good soup mixture.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix meat with next 6 ingredients and shape into balls about the size of a quarter or a little bit larger.
Brown meatballs in shortening and drain off excess fat.
Mix in cornstarch and sugar; stir in syrup from pineapple, the vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook on medium heat until it boils.
Add meatballs and green pepper; cook 10 to 15 minutes on medium heat or until mixture thickens.
Add pineapple and serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix softened butter (margarine) and sugar together with mixer. Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Stir in bananas. Add flour; mix well.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix butter, sour cream, cream cheese and lemon juice, then add sugar and pecans.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak in butter with fresh mushrooms.
Put in pan, reserving juice.
Add sour cream, soup and canned mushrooms, if you don't use fresh.
Mix and add a little bit of the meat juice. Don't add too much of the juice because as it simmers, it thins down. Cook low for 45 minutes or until tender. Serve over egg noodles. Serves 4 to 5.

title: zesty chicken
directions: Mix preserves, juice and soy sauce.
Coat chicken.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Top with melted butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mama's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour in pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.
When a knife is inserted, should come out clean.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine everything except cheese, oleo and stuffing.
Pour into greased dish; top with cheese.
Melt butter and stir in crumbs.
Spread over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
This recipe is easily doubled and will serve 8 to 10 people.

title: sausage pancakes
directions: Crumble sausage and brown.
Place on paper towel to drain. Combine other ingredients and mix well in large bowl.
Add sausage and stir until mixed.
Cook on hot griddle or skillet with enough oil to prevent sticking.
Pancake will be thick, but light.

title: fantastic salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and allow to set up before serving.

title: vickie's baked beans
directions: Mix together and place in greased dish.
Bake slowly at 300° for 2 hours, or until set.

title: kahlua(makes 5 cups)
directions: Combine sugar, water and instant coffee in saucepan.
Boil slowly until syrupy, about 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add vodka and vanilla bean.
Pour into jar(s).
Age at least 3 weeks in a cool, dark place.

title: quiche
directions: Beat eggs.
Add soup and cream.
Mix well.
Sprinkle meat, cheese and broccoli evenly in bottom of pie crust.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until center is set.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: multi-grained bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in sequence. Let sit. Take care to keep batter warm enough for yeast. (Put bowl in sink of hot water.) Add 1/2 of each type of flour. Stir in. Let sit while greasing 3 loaf pans. Add remaining flour. Remove from bowl. Knead about 80 times. Place in another oiled bowl. Keep in warm place, covered, for 30 minutes or until double in bulk. Punch down. Knead again just enough to get all bubbles out. Divide dough into thirds and let rise in loaf pans for 15 minutes. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: night before french toast casserole
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut bread into thick slices and arrange in one layer in pan.
In large bowl beat eggs with remaining ingredients except oleo.
When thoroughly mixed, pour over bread.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 4 to 36 hours.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Place first 6 ingredients in saucepan and warm together, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place a layer of Doritos, crushing slightly.
Add a layer of cooked chicken.
Add layer of the soup mixture.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Cover with cheese.
Bake for about 30 minutes, until hot and bubbly and cheese has melted. Will serve
8 people adequately.

title: sausage spinach souffle
directions: Mix and pour all ingredients into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: Combine all the ingredients in blender.
Process until thoroughly mixed.
Chill for several hours.
Garnish with chopped chives.
Makes 2 cups.

title: marinated deer steak
directions: Put uncooked deer in a pan.
Add Italian seasoning to deer steak and leave overnight.
Roll deer in flour.
Fry until brown. Put in pan, then pour cream of mushroom soup over steak.
Put in oven at 450° and bake for 45 minutes.
Take out and serve.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Add cold water to liquid to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid.
Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened. Stir in whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound; stir in oranges, pineapple, marshmallows and coconut.
Spoon into a 6 cup mold. Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Unmold.
Makes 10 servings.

title: pork chops and stuffing
directions: Butter a long baking dish.
Place potatoes on bottom, then pork chops.
Mix soup with milk and pour over the potatoes and pork chops.
Add diced onion and then sprinkle Pepperidge stuffing mix over top.
Top with some melted margarine.
Cover dish and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Scald the milk; add the syrup and salt.
Add 2 cups of flour and beat well.
Add yeast mix. Beat eggs; add them.
Blend well and add the shortening and remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth and satiny.
Place in a lightly greased bowl.
Grease top of dough. Cover and put into refrigerator.
When wanted, remove dough from refrigerator and punch down.
Remove desired amount.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Pinch off desired amounts for rolls. Place the rolls in greased pans and let rolls rise until double in size.
Bake in moderately hot oven (375°) for approximately 20 minutes.

title: martha washington bonbons
directions: Combine sugar and butter until well blended.
Divide and add strawberry flavoring and red food coloring to 1/2.
To remaining candy, add 2 to 3 drops of mint flavoring and green food coloring. Cover and set aside.
Melt chocolate and wax in top of double boiler.
Pinch small amounts of candy and roll into a ball. Continue until all candy is ready.
Place on cookie sheet and refrigerate until ready to dip.
Using a candy fork or toothpick, dip each ball in chocolate coating and return to pan.
Store in airtight tin.

title: sarah's cheese cake
directions: Mix everything but graham cracker crust in a medium size bowl. Mix at high speed until well blended.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Boil sugar, corn syrup and water until mixture spins threads. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour hot mixture into egg whites, beating constantly with electric mixer, pouring slowly while beating.
When it begins to stiffen, add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Brown sausage with bell pepper, onion and celery until tender. Mix soup and rice in mixing bowl.
Add meat mixture.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: shrimp ala creole
directions: In a large high-walled skillet or wok, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add the onions, bell pepper and parsley; saute until the onions are clear.
Stir in the wine, tomatoes, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, tomato sauce, salt, mint and pepper.
Cover and cook over medium heat until the sauce comes to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 1 hour until the tomatoes fall apart.
Add the shrimp and continue simmering 30 minutes or more, stirring occasionally.
Serve over cooked rice or pasta or use as an omelette filling.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Beat eggs very light; add sugar gradually and beat until fluffy.
Add
cream
and
vanilla;
beat.
Sift dry ingredients together
3 times and add to egg mixture, beating until smooth. Bake in an 8-inch square pan lined with waxed paper.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: peppered roast beef
directions: In a small bowl, combine spices and mix well.
Rub meat with olive oil and spices until well coated with spice mixture.
Place roast on rack.
Bake at 500° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake additional 45 minutes or until internal temperature reaches 130° for rare.
Makes about 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberries
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for 1 hour. Shape into strawberries and roll in colored sugar.
Decorate with dab of green frosting and half of toothpick dipped in green coloring for leaves and stem.

title: davinci acini di pepe salad
directions: Cook macaroni for 30 minutes and drain well.
Drain fruit. Heat juice.
Add flour, sugar and beaten eggs until thickened. Combine thickened juice and macaroni. Let set to cool well.
Add fruit, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate to set.

title: diabetic apple pie
directions: Combine apple juice concentrate and cornstarch; cook until thickened.
Add butter, salt and cinnamon.
Add sliced apples; mix well.
Turn into pastry-lined pie pan.
Cover with top crust. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seasoned dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together; serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: tricia's one skillet lemon chicken
directions: Dip chicken in flour.
In large skillet, heat oil and oleo over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook 5 minutes on each side. Remove and set aside.
In same skillet, stir lemon juice and parsley into oil and oleo mixture.
Pour over chicken.
Keep warm. In same skillet, prepare Rice-A-Roni mix as directed.
Stir in broccoli after rice has simmered 10 minutes.
Top with chicken, parsley and lemon sauce; sprinkle with cheese.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add milk and mix well.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well. Add oatmeal, Rice Krispies and coconut.
Drop on cookie sheets and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: lime salad
directions: Put jello in large container.
Add boiling water and stir 2 minutes.
Add cold water and pineapple juice.
Stir and put in refrigerator.
Just before it is solid, add pineapple, cottage cheese and Miracle Whip.
Mix this with beater just until well blended, then put back in refrigerator until solid.

title: classic coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrots and onion in a large mixing bowl. Sprinkle with sugar.
In cup, mix mayonnaise and vinegar.
Stir until blended and pour over cabbage mixture.
Stir thoroughly. Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: peking roast
directions: Cut slits completely through the meat. Insert slivers of garlic down into the slits. Can use onions instead of garlic. Both garlic and onions are best. Pour 1 cup cider vinegar over meat. Make sure it runs down into the slits where the garlic and onions are. Onion buds are ideal. Put this in the refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: crunchy no-fry chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Dip chicken in broth then into corn flake mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: grandma's spicy beans
directions: Cook pinto beans until almost done, then add salt and pepper. Add chopped vegetables, garlic and bay leaf.
Bring beans to a boil, then add 1 pound of ground beef that has been made into walnut-sized balls and browned until done.
Add Ro-Tel and simmer until all ingredients are done.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine.
In separate bowl, mix pudding with milk.
Add Cool Whip and then cream cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Crumble cookies.
In medium size (approximately 1 gallon size) planter, layer cookie crumbs, pudding mixture, cookies, etc.
Top with cookies.
Cool before serving. Decorate with silk flowers so that end result looks like potted plant.

title: beef cracker spread
directions: Cream the cheese and milk.
Add beef and onion.
Add sour cream.
Put in pie plate.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: cracker salad
directions: Crush crackers.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill in bowl and serve on lettuce.
If too dry, add just a little vinegar from the pickles.
This salad will keep at least a week covered in the refrigerator.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Add potatoes, celery, carrots and onion to pot of water.
Boil until vegetables are soft.
Drain water; mash potatoes.
Add butter, chicken soup, milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat. While heating, add cheese.
Stir frequently.

title: cuban chicken fricassee(fricase de pollo cubano)
directions: Wash the chicken and remove the skin if you like.
You can brown the chicken pieces in oil and then add the sofrito and water or if you're in a hurry, you can cook the chicken in the sofrito and water and delete the browning step.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix in large bowl.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add pizza sauce and tomato sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add a dash of salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Cook noodles as directed.
In a large casserole dish, layer meat sauce, noodles and cheese.
Top with cheese and slices of pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: maple syrup
directions: Bring sugars, water and salt to a boil; turn down to simmer with cover on for 10 minutes.
Add vanilla and maple flavoring. Serve.

title: shell macaroni salad
directions: Mix macaroni and vegetables, except peas.
Put French dressing over and let stand in refrigerator.
Just before serving, add peas and nutmeats.
You may want to add more dressing.
Cover with grated cheese and sliced stuffed olives.

title: sweet mustard lamb
directions: In a bowl combine margarine, honey, mustard, rosemary and pepper.
Trim excess fat from the lamb chops.
Place the lamb chops on a rack in a shallow baking pan.
Brush with some of the honey mixture.
Roast in a 325° oven until desired doneness (allow about 35 to 40 minutes for medium doneness).
Before serving the lamb chops, brush each chop with a little of the honey mixture again.
Top each lamb chop with fresh chives, if desired.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: vanilla wafer cookies
directions: In saucepan, cream together sugar and butter.
Then add eggs, nuts, pineapple and dates.
Cook until thick.
Just before removing from stove, add vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Spread between vanilla wafers.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: iced mocha
directions: In medium bowl, combine hot Espresso, skim milk, chocolate extract and sugar.
Let cool.

title: mamie eisenhower's fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter.
Boil for 6 minutes only.
In a bowl, place chocolates and marshmallow.
Add the boiling mixture and stir until all is dissolved.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Beat egg white and water until fluffy.
Place pecans in egg white mixture to coat.
Then coat pecans with sugar, cinnamon and salt mixture.

title: apricot bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture.
Add coconut and nuts.
Mix well.
Press 2/3 mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread with preserves.
Crumble remaining dough over top.
If mixture isn't crumbly enough, I add some more sugar and flour Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
Cool and cut.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, margarine and Milnot.
Boil 5 minutes. Stir frequently.
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Fluff and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with fudge ice cream topping.
Chill.

title: mixed vegetables
directions: Same as Navy Bean Pottage, but delete cabbage and pumpkin.
Use potatoes or add one large green plantain.
Add 1/4 teaspoon black pepper.

title: divinity
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, syrup, salt and water. Cook to hard ball stage (260°); stir only until sugar dissolves. It will take 8 to 10 minutes to reach hard ball stage.
I use a thermometer to monitor temperature and cold water to test after it reaches 250° to make doubly sure it's at the right stage.

title: hershey's prize chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round pans.
Cream butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs.
Combine baking soda, cocoa, baking powder and salt in bowl. Add alternately with milk to batter.
Blend well.
Pour into pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes. Remove from pans.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: In a large bowl combine eggs and sugar; beat well.
Add oil, flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, pumpkin and vanilla.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
When cooling cake, keep out of draft.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Add egg whites to mixing bowl and beat well.
Pour in milk and mix.
Mix dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Add dry ingredients to liquid ingredients.
Stir until moist.
Fill 12 greased or paper-lined muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 muffins, 80 calories per serving.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: Crust:
Mix pecans, flour and butter.
Put on bottom of Pyrex pan.
Bake at 400° until light brown; let cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until clear and thick. Set off.
Pour Jell-O out of package into mixture.
Add strawberries and pour into baked pie crust.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Or cook in crock-pot. Serve warm with chips, Fritos, crackers or breadsticks.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and press.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix well.
This dip is particularly good with vegetables.

title: aunt ruth's garden relish(corn relish)
directions: Cook for one hour.
Seal in jars hot.
Makes 4 pints.
(If doubling, use less vinegar, but keep the sugar and vinegar at least equal.)
Add more sugar if you want the relish sweeter.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix spinach, water chestnuts, soup mix, sour cream, mayonnaise and onions.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Makes about 3 cups dip.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix together molasses, shortening, eggs, milk and baking soda. Add flour to mixture. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients in 5-quart glass dish.
Cook in microwave on High 12 minutes, stirring at 4 minute intervals. Take out.
Stir in soda.
Cook 1 minute.
Beat one minute.
Drop onto aluminum foil.
Let stand for 1 hour.

title: no crust zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Butter a 10 or 11-inch pie plate generously and pour mixture into pie plate. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden on top.

title: creamed chicken in puff pastry
directions: Saute mushrooms in 1 tablespoon butter and set aside.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet and add flour to make a roux.
Add milk slowly until mixture thickens, then add chicken broth. Season and add mushroom mixture and chicken and heat on low until hot.
Bake pastry shells as directed on package.
Serve inside shells.

title: basic rice
directions: Combine the ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and cook on High for 3 to 5 minutes, or until boiling; then on Medium for 7 to 10 minutes, or until most of the water is absorbed.
Stir and let stand, covered, for 3 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole no. 2
directions: Slice and
cook zucchini in 2 cups water for 5 minutes. Drain. While
zucchini drains, beat eggs until foamy in large bowl. Stir in mayonnaise, chopped onion and salt.
Add cheese until well
blended.
Pour
into
cup
shallow
casserole. Sprinkle with
bread
crumbs.
Dot
with
more small pieces of butter or margarine.
Bake
in
a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Saute onions in a little butter or olive oil.
Add all other ingredients except Parmesan.
Stir in spaghetti and place in a large casserole dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan over top.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into muffin pan.
Bake at 350° until brown, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: orange slice bars(without shortening)
directions: Cut orange slices with scissors dipped in water and add to flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Toss lightly to coat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut in bars or squares and roll in granulated sugar.
Makes 24 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut up chicken into bite-size pieces (put in casserole dish.) Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Spread cheese over soup mix. Mix a can of soup with milk.
Pour over ingredients.
Melt stick of butter (or margarine) and mix it with stuffing mix.
Pour mix (butter and stuffing) over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with pasta or vegetable.

title: sponge cake(from 1975 edition)
directions: Put cornstarch and baking powder in cup; fill cup with flour. Separate eggs; beat yolks with sugar, water and lemon juice until light and lemon colored with no trace of grains of sugar.
Add flour to egg yolk mixture; stir lightly.
Beat egg whites until very stiff, then fold in yolk mixture.
Pour in small tube pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and milk; add eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder and add to mixture.
Add lemon extract and coconut. Place in tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Marinate wings overnight; turn occasionally.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°; do not cover.

title: spaetzel
directions: Bring water and bouillon to boil.
In a bowl, beat flour, butter, water, salt and eggs until smooth.
Reduce heat to medium; press dough into simmering water; can use a colander to do this. Stir gently.
Cook until dough rises and is tender.
Drain and serve.

title: lemon pepper winglets
directions: Cut wing-tip joints from chicken wings.
(Use for making broth, if desired.)
Cut the remaining V-shaped wings at the joints to make "winglets"; set aside.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in a greased 6-cup muffin pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 biscuits.

title: no-cook divinity
directions: Beat frosting mix (dry), corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water in small bowl on high speed about 5 minutes or until stiff peaks form.
Transfer to large bowl; gradually beat in sugar on low speed.
(It may be necessary to stir in last cup of sugar by hand.) Stir in nuts.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand at room temperature at least 12 hours, turning candy over once, until outside of candy is firm.
Makes approximately 5 1/2 dozen candies.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend the peanut butter, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Fold in the Cool Whip. Pour into a baked pie crust. Top with hot fudge chocolate sauce.

title: mexican chocolate crinkles
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in syrup and chocolate. Stir flour, soda, salt and cinnamon into creamed mixture and stir to make a stiff dough.
Shape dough into balls and roll in sugar. Place on ungreased pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Put 2 heads of dill in each jar.
Pour hot solution over cucumbers packed in jar.
Seal hot in tight jars.
Wait at least 60 days before eating.

title: cheese pie
directions: Crust:
Crush 12 to 14 Zwieback.
Melt 1/2 stick butter.
Mix with Zwieback.
Press into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Mix rest of ingredients and add wet ingredients. Pour into cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let cool.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: tempera paint mixer
directions: Combine ingredients.
This makes a thicker poster paint.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Saute garlic and onion in a little bit of olive oil.
Add beef broth, wine and water.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Add chopped carrots and celery.
Simmer for another 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes, zucchini, tomato paste, sugar, pepper and parsley.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add kidney beans and thawed tortellini.
Cook until beans and tortellini are done.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in pie shell and top with whipped cream.

title: chicken squares
directions: Boil the chicken breasts and take off bone if needed.
Cut the chicken into small pieces (i.e. for chicken salad); combine the chicken pieces, cream cheese, onion, milk and salt and pepper (to taste) in a mixing bowl.
Take crescent rolls out of fridge. Divide them into squares (keeping 2 of them together at a time). One package of 8 rolls will end up making 4 squares.
Smooth out the perforated edge (which will run through the middle of the square).
Next, use your fingers to push the dough outward expanding the size of the square.
Melt the cube of butter.
With a pastry brush or spoon, spread a layer of melted butter over the square.

Next, spoon some of the chicken mixture onto the square, then take opposite corners and bring them up toward each other and pinch them together so the chicken mixture is inside the square. Pinch the seams together down the sides.
Place all the squares this way on a baking sheet and bake at approximately 325° until the tops begin to turn golden and split open.
Take them out and baste them with the butter and quickly pour some bread crumbs over them.
Return them to the oven until they are a deeper golden brown and slightly crunchy on top.
You may want to serve them with rice or a fresh vegetable.

title: shrimp saute
directions: If shrimp are frozen, put into strainer and run cold water over them until they can be separated.
Drain.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bring water to a boil; add salt.
Add rice and stir once. Cover, turn heat to low and cook for 20 minutes or until water is absorbed.

title: pound cake
directions: Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350° in a loaf pan.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Pour tomatoes into baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Add bread cubes.
Stir gently to mix well.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple chess pie with pecans
directions: Place the flour, salt and sugar in a large bowl; blend well with a fork.
Add the oil and, using a pastry blender or 2 table knives, cut the oil into the flour until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle the water and milk over the mixture; blend it with a knife.
Using your hands, gather the dough into 2 balls.
Use immediately, or wrap with plastic wrap and refrigerate until needed.
When rolling the dough out, roll it between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Yields 2 (9-inch) single crust pies (16 slices).

title: quaker oat butterscotch cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat the margarine or butter and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add combined flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Press dough onto bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish and bake 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: clam chowder
directions: Chop onion.
Saute in margarine until tender.
Add water and potatoes, celery, clams, salt and pepper.
Cook about 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add celery soup and milk.
Simmer approximately 30 minutes.

title: quick chicken quiche
directions: In the pie shell, place the chicken.
Saute mushrooms in butter for 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheeses over pie.
Beat eggs and cream together.
Add parsley and salt to the cream mixture.
Pour over cheese mixture and bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with a tossed salad.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice carrots crosswise and cook in salted water 10 minutes. Drain and cool.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook together 5 minutes.
Add sugar, vinegar, corn oil, tomato soup, let marinate for 24 hours or longer.
Will keep for 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine cocoa, flour, sugar and salt in a saucepan. Add eggs and stir. Turn heat on medium and gradually add in milk. Boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. When mixture thickens, remove from heat and add butter and vanilla. Cool and pour into baked pie shell.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken in electric skillet.
Salt and pepper to taste. Pour equal amounts of barbecue sauce and Coke in bowl and stir until blended (judge this on the number of pieces of chicken you serve).
Pour mixture over chicken and set skillet on simmer or low.
Cover and check often.
Sauce will thicken and should cook within an hour.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla together until smooth. Add flour and mix well. Add remaining ingredients and pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 10 minutes.

title: crepes
directions: Whip all ingredients in a mixing bowl with a wire whisk.
Pour onto greased skillet, making about a 7 or 8-inch diameter crepe. Once lightly browned, flip once.
Serve with your favorite jelly or jam rolled in the crepe.
This recipe will make approximately 4 crepes.

title: coconut cream cookies
directions: Beat until
fluffy first 6 ingredients.
Add rest.
Mix and form
into	balls.	Press
down
on greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pig picker cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Fold in oranges.
Bake in 3 greased layer pans at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: linguine alla carbonara
directions: Let eggs, cream and butter or margarine stand at room temperature for 2 to 3 hours.
Fry the bacon in a skillet until brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Beat eggs and cream together just until blended.

title: oscar's simple roast
directions: *Note:
This is a very lean roast.

title: crunch cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.

title: ethiopian bars
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut into 3 dozen squares.
Roll each square in powdered sugar.

title: deep peach pie
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add well beaten egg and beat thoroughly.
Mix and sift dry ingredients, then add alternately with the milk to creamed mixture.
Fill the buttered baking dish (a deep dish) with the sliced peaches.
Pour batter over the peaches and bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: golden parmesan baked potatoes
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese in butter (to taste).
Turn potatoes upside-down in this mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and condensed milk.
Pour in evaporated milk and regular milk to fill line in freezer container.
Add vanilla and freeze according to instructions. Enjoy!

title: crabmeat appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Spread on split muffin halves.
Cut each muffin into 8 pie shaped wedges. You will end up with 128 sections.
Place, not touching, on cookie sheets and freeze.
Place frozen sections in freezer bags until ready to bake.
Bake frozen sections on ungreased cookie sheet at 300° for 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: creamed chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water until done.
Cool and debone. Place chicken in an 8 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook onion and celery in a small amount of butter until tender.
Pour over chicken.
Mix cream of chicken soup with broth; pour over chicken. Top with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until top is brown.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for about one hour or until the celery and onion are done.
For a large crowd, you may double this recipe.

title: jello salad
directions: Put marshmallows in large bowl and mix in cocktail.
Let set overnight or all day in refrigerator.
Mix pineapple with cream cheese and whipped cream.
Mix with other ingredients.
Mix well. Keep in refrigerator.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Add vanilla flavoring as desired.
Layer into bowl with wafers, bananas and pudding, ending with pudding on top.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: lobster pasta
directions: Blanch lobster tails in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Remove and put in cold water.
Remove meat from shells and slice into 1/4-inch pieces.
In saute pan over medium heat, cook lobster and shallots in 1 ounce of olive oil for 2 minutes.
Remove lobster and add wine and cream.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Add ginger and basil and simmer 1 minute longer.
Add butter and lobster and mix well.
Add marinara, salt and pepper.
Toss cooked pasta with remaining olive oil.
Add to sauce and toss again.
Serves 4 as a first course.

title: sandwich filling
directions: Combine all ingredients and use as a filling between lightly buttered slices of thin sliced white loaf bread. Trim crust; cut each sandwich in 4 triangles. Makes 1 3/4 cups filling. Put about 1/4 cup of filling in 1 sandwich if you want it to be thick. Do not substitute and do not leave out any ingredients and even though this sounds strange, it is so good. Do not use a food processor to chop.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: peanut delight
directions: First Layer: Mix together and press into the bottom of a 9x13x2 pan the graham cracker crumbs, melted butter and nuts.

title: banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray muffin pan cups with nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl, stir flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg to mix well.
Stir in nuts; set aside.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain liquid off corn, peas and beans.
Mix vegetables in a large bowl.
Place vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and water in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Then allow to cool.
Pour over vegetables and let them chill in refrigerator overnight.
Salad will keep for several weeks in refrigerator.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Combine above ingredients; beat. Place on greased, waxed paper, on cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 5 minutes. Invert on new waxed paper. Fill, roll & refrigerate 1 hour.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice onions and cucumbers.
Soak in ice water with salt added for 3 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients; add cucumber and onions.
Just heat through.
Put in jars and seal.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Combine flour, sugar and juice from crushed pineapple.
Add 1 well beaten egg and cider vinegar.
Cook 2 minutes on High in microwave and stir.
Repeat 1 or more times until thick like custard. Cool.
Peel and chunk apples.
Pour cooled mixture over apples.
Mix well and add pineapple.
Fold in container of Cool Whip and salted peanuts.

title: cheese pie
directions: Beat egg whites first; set aside.
Mix cheese, sugar, yolks, flour and butter.
Mix good, then add milk slowly.
Beat in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour into prepared crust in pan.

title: blueberry almond crunch
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Cut in butter with pastry blender until crumbly. Stir in chopped walnuts. Press 1/2 of mixture in 8 x 8 pan. Stir almond extract into blueberry pie filling.	Pour over crumb mixture. Spread to edges. Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve warm or cold with ice cream.

title: gram's squash cookies
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together and let set the cream cheese and sugar.
Add frozen strawberries, crushed pineapple and sliced bananas.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze well.
If you freeze in loaf pans, then you can slice to serve.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken into egg whites.
On waxed paper, coat chicken with crumbs.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove; set aside.
In same skillet, heat spaghetti sauce to boiling.
Add chicken.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley. Cover; cook until cheese is melted.
Serve with spaghetti.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and Bisquick until smooth.
Fold in broccoli and cheese.
Pour in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake until knife inserted and comes out clean (approximately 1 hour).

title: chicken with lemon
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl.
Marinate for 3 to 4 hours in the refrigerator.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or broil for 45 minutes. Baste with marinade liquid.

title: no-peek beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in crockpot; stir together well. Cover and cook, on low, 8-12 hours.
On high 4-6 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 4.
This recipe can be doubled.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
This will keep in a jar really good.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes and fry in shortening.
Brown on both sides until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Boil peppers, sugar and vinegar 3 minutes.
Add Certo and food coloring.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter in a skillet over medium heat.
Add onion, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Cook, stirring constantly, 5 minutes. Stir in crawfish, salt, pepper, onion powder and Tabasco.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in flour; cook, stirring constantly, 2 minutes. Stir in water; cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes.
Stir in green onions and parsley; cook 3 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt carob chips in double boiler.
Add peanut butter and stir in rolled oats.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet and freeze.
May be served frozen or room temperature. While carob chips do contain sugar, this treat satisfies a chocolate craving without the caffeine.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine pumpkin, raisins, sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cookies are real soft.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in dish, place chicken over rice and other ingredients over chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken quesadillas with barbecue chipotle sauce
directions: Chop cooked chicken.
Add scallions, cilantro and 1/2 of the barbecue sauce.
Spread on 1/2 of flour tortillas.
Cover with Jack cheese.
Put other flour tortillas on top.
Brown in a large dry saute pan on medium heat (approximately 3 to 5 minutes each). Cut quesadillas into 6 sections.
Serve and enjoy.

title: a nice cup of tea
directions: Boil a kettle of water.
As soon as the water boils, pour sufficient water into teapot to allow you to swish it about to clean out any residue left after the previous brewing.
This also warms the teapot.
Throw away the water.
Place 1 1/2 - 2 teaspoons of tea leaves into the pot and immediately fill with boiled water. Stir with a teaspoon.
Replace lid of teapot and cover teapot with the cozy.
This will keep the tea hot for a very long time. If you use American tea, for some reason weaker than most English blends, you may need to use 3 - 4 teaspoons per pot.

title: toasted cinnamon pecans
directions: Melt margarine in large glass dish in microwave for about 1 minute, covered with wax paper.
Stir in pecans, sugar and cinnamon until thoroughly mixed and coated.
Cook on High for 4 minutes, stirring every minute.
Let drain on paper towel.
Store in tightly covered jar.

title: strawberry cheesecake pie
directions: Preheat oven to 550°.
To prepare crust, combine cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and margarine; mix well.
Press with the back of a spoon into the bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan; set aside.

To prepare filling, place in a food processor or electric mixer the Ricotta cheese, flour, orange peel, vanilla, eggs, yogurt and remaining 1/3 cup sugar; process until smooth. Pour into prepared crust.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 200°.
Bake until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean, about 25 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool completely.
Hull and cut strawberries in halves.
Arrange cut side down on the cheese filling.
In a small saucepan combine currant jelly and water; cook and stir until melted and smooth.
Spoon over strawberries. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: goulash
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box. Brown meat and onion. Add chili sauce and tomato soup.
Add drained and cooked macaroni.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Drain grease from meat before adding other ingredients.
Serves 2 or 3.

title: jalapeno fritters
directions: Cut tops from jalapeno peppers, cut out all seed but leave whole.
Stuff with sour cream.
Dip in batter, roll in breading and deep fry until golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: quick peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Arrange peaches in square pan (8 x 8 x 8-inch).
Mix baking mix, brown sugar, cinnamon and margarine with fork.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake until light brown, about 20 minutes.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.
Makes six servings.

title: lace cookies
directions: Mix together and drop on cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Do not mash down.
They will become very thin and crisp (spread out as they bake).
You may want to spray pans and let cookie slightly cool before taking them off.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or less.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Cut sausage links in 1/4-inch slices.
Cut bread into 1-inch pieces.
Brown sausage in large skillet; drain well and set aside. Place bread into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top bread pieces with cheese and sausage.
Combine 2 cups milk and next 4 ingredients in large bowl and pour over top of bread mixture.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Combine soup with 1/2 cup milk and pour over casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve casserole immediately.

title: fondue italiano
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce mix and tomato sauce.
Heat.
Add cheeses, a little at a time, and stir until melted.
Mix cornstarch and wine.
Add to sauce mix.
Transfer to fondue pot.
Dip bread into sauce.

title: barbara's dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage. Drain well. Put in crock pot with cheese and tomatoes; let melt. Serve with chips.

title: phyllis' pfantasy pfudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan; bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat and add chocolate bits; stir until melted in.
Add marshmallows, nuts and vanilla; beat until blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let all cheeses stand at room temperature.
Stir cheeses together.
Add and mix all the ingredients except 1/2 cup nuts. Refrigerate until chilled.
Shape into a ball and roll over 1/2 cup nuts and 1/4 cup parsley flakes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix margarine with crushed cookies.
Put half of the mixture in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread 1/2 gallon ice cream (softened) on top of cookies.
Drizzle syrup over ice cream.
Spread Cool Whip over syrup.
Sprinkle remaining cookies over Cool Whip. Freeze overnight.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine and shortening.
Add sugar; beat well.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift flour with soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Warm applesauce slightly and stir in soda.
Add sugar and oleo and stir mixture well; then add flour, sifted with spices.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour in tube pan, bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Let cool in pan for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Chop squash finely, about the size of small peas.
Blend all ingredients thoroughly and press into greased 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 370° for 25 minutes.
Cut and serve while hot.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in boiling water to cover, about 20 minutes. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into greased casserole. Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 30 minutes or until browned. For 6.

title: gorp
directions: Mix all together and place in a tightly closed container.

title: fish and chips
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into 1/2-inch strips.
Cut fish into 2 x 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Heat oil (2 to 3 inches deep) in deep fryer to 375°.
Fill basket 1/4 full with potatoes.
Slowly lower into hot oil (if oil bubbles excessively, raise and lower basket several times).
Use long handled fork to keep potatoes separate.
Fry potatoes until golden, 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain potatoes.
Place in single layer on cookie sheet (keep warm).
Repeat with rest of potatoes.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until mixture spins a thread. Gradually pour into stiffly beaten egg whites, beating continually.
As soon as mixture begins to thicken, stop beating with electric mixer.
Add vanilla and finish with a spoon.
Stop when mixture holds its shape when dropped from spoon.
Stick pecan half on top.

title: pecan roast
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 400° for 5 minutes, then turn to 300° for 35 minutes or until firm.

title: pepper steak
directions: Coat steak with flour.
Brown in hot oil in Dutch oven until golden brown.
Drain oil.
Cover with water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until meat is tender and gravy is thick. Serve over rice, noodles or potatoes.

title: pentecost cake
directions: You will also need a candle and the New Testament.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, pumpkin and vanilla.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoons onto well-greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from cookie sheets while still warm and cool on racks.

title: chinese style chicken curry
directions: In a large pan or wok, brown oil, onion, dried chillies, garlic, salt, ginger and tomato.
Add some water and stir to make a soup.
Add chicken; cook completely over low heat.
Cover.
Add soy, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight. Roll into balls. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate with toothpicks onto wax paper.

title: cornish hens a la joyce
directions: Tear off enough squares of foil to enclose the birds.
On each square of foil, put 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Rub the birds around in it.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place meat side down.
Mix herbs, wine and Worcestershire; put in cavity of each bird.
Wrap each tightly in foil.
Place on cookie sheet in 300° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
At this point, turn the oven down and hold up to at least 3 hours.
Before I serve, I put a ball of good dressing in cavity of bird and cook for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and pour over chicken parts.
Cover with foil and bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 325 degrees. Makes enough sauce to cover several pounds of meat.

title: sausage wontons
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Add green and red peppers, olives, dressing mix, sour cream and cheeses.
Stir together.
Lightly brush wonton wrappers with olive oil, leaving almost no oil on shell.
Place shells into muffin tin cups.
Bake empty for 5 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Fill shells with about a tablespoon of sausage mixture.
Return filled shells to the oven for 6 to 7 minutes or until the cheeses have melted and the shells are golden brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Mix all ingredients, but add Fritos at serving time.

title: apple tapioca ala mode
directions: Let stand 5 minutes.
Bring to boil.
Simmer until tender or bake at 350° until tender.
Serve warm with sprinkle of nutmeg and scoop of ice cream.

title: caramel layer bars
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat until melted.
Stir often.
Keep warm.
Combine remaining ingredients except chips.
Stir by hand until well mixed (reserve 1 cup crumbs).
Press 1/2 dough in 9 x 13-inch cake pan, greased and floured.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle chips over baked crust. Spread caramel mixture over all.
Crumble reserved dough over caramel mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: greek bread
directions: Cut French bread in half lengthwise.
Mix other ingredients well and spread over bread.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats in small bowl.
Let stand, covered, for 20 minutes.
Beat butter in large mixer bowl until light.
Add sugar and brown sugar gradually, beating until fluffy. Add vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Stir in oats.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together.
Stir into oats mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake tests done.
Spread frosting over top of cake.
Bake until bubbly.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: best ever chicken
directions: Mix dressing, apricot jam and soup and pour over chicken in large baking dish.
Baste every 20 minutes for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, 1 egg, 1 teaspoon vanilla and salt until thoroughly blended.
In separate bowl beat 3 eggs, 1/4 cup sugar, syrup and 1 teaspoon vanilla until well blended. Spread cream cheese mixture in bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle in pecans.
Carefully pour in syrup mixture.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for approximately 40 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again. In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Toss lightly. Transfer to large salad bowl.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple cream salad mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and let gel slightly.
Fold in sour cream, salt, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into mold and let set for at least 3 hours.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Thaw pastry 20 minutes.
On a lightly floured surface, roll to a 15 1/2 x 9-inch rectangle.
Cut into 3 strips, each 3-inches wide.
Divide sausage meat into thirds; roll each into a "snake" the length of the pastry.
Place each roll along one edge of a pastry strip.
Roll the pastry around the sausage.
Wet edges with ice water and press and seal tightly.
Chill the rolls for 1 hour. Cut sausage rolls into 3/4-inch slices; placed on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes or until pastry is puffed and golden.
Serve warm.
Makes about 60 hors d'oeuvres.

title: hamburger sausage
directions: This recipe is easy to do, but does take about 24 hours from start to finish.
It is well worth the time.

title: crunch cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Put ingredients in heavy 1-quart saucepan.
Stir over low heat until chocolate melts completely.
Serve over ice cream or cake. This can be reheated.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Mix in order given and bake in a greased and floured tube pan or Bundt cake pan at 375° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: great potatoes
directions: Take the can of chicken soup, warmed with the stick of oleo. Mix all together.
Put in greased 13-inch cake pan.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Great with pork chops.

title: date pie
directions: Beat the sugar with eggs, then put into milk.
Bake in single crust.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry bacon and sausage well; drain grease and crumble.
In a large bowl, crack eggs and beat.
Stir in cheeses, salt, pepper, bacon and sausage.
Crumble bread and stir into mixture.
Pour into greased baking pan.
Add enough milk to make soupy and stir through mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour, until firm and cooked away from sides.

title: noodle pudding (kugel)(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Beat eggs.
Add salt, sugar, cottage cheese, cream cheese, melted butter, sour cream, milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
