Stir in noodles and mix thoroughly.
Stir in raisins.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix all ingredients with a mixer.

title: elegant sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening, gradually adding sugar, beating well.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Saute pepper, onion and celery in margarine.
Mix beans, corn, soup, cheese, sour cream and sauteed vegetables; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Just before taking out of oven, sprinkle with Cheese Nips and almonds.

title: low country boil
directions: Excellent traditional Southern dish that even I can make.

title: sausage balls
directions: Break sausage up into small pieces.
Mix sausage, cheese and Bisquick in large mixing bowl.
Roll out into approximately 1-inch balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Use Dijon mustard to dip sausage balls in.

title: capellini toscano
directions: Melt butter with olive oil in frying pan.
Saute spinach for 10 minutes.
Add diced ham, saute 10 minutes.
Add marinara sauce; simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in grated cheese and cream.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Serve over cooked and well drained capellini.

title: easy crumb cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Spread in oblong greased pan. Bake as directed about 1/2 suggested time.
Remove from oven.

title: double crust pie pastry
directions: In medium bowl, stir flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until pieces are the size of small peas.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon water over part of mixture; gently toss.
Repeat until all is moistened. Form into 2 balls.
On lightly floured surface, flatten 1 ball of dough with hands.
Roll with floured pin from center to edges. Ease pastry into pie plate (so not to tear).
Trim pastry even with pie plate rim.
Repeat with remaining ball for top crust or use for single crust pie as well.
Use fingers to pinch and shape pie edges.
(Can use about 1 tablespoon of sugar in recipe as well.
It gives a much better, sweeter flavor.)

title: brown sugar crisps
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll dough into balls about the size of a walnut and roll balls in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; beat well.
Set aside.

title: meringue(per pie)
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and water. Beat until stiff and in peaks.
Add sugar, 1 or 2 at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Beat until very stiff.
Spread over pie.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; let thicken slightly.
Mix pineapple, cranberry sauce and pecans.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream, adding a small amount of fruit juice from the fruit mixture; blend well.
Stir into gelatin.
Chill overnight.
Salad will keep for a week in refrigerator.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Cream salad dressing and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and beat all together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: five-layer bean dip
directions: In baking dish or 3-inch high bowl, layer beans, then chilies, then sour cream, then cheese.
Sprinkle tomatoes and onions on top.
Serve with tortilla chips for dipping.

title: bavarian salad
directions: Mix marshmallows and jello in hot water.
Allow to cool until it begins to thicken.
Add nuts, cheese and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix lime jello, boiling water and pineapple.
Allow to congeal.
Meanwhile, soften cream cheese.
Spread cream cheese, salad dressing and pecans over lime mixture and allow to cool. Mix jello and boiling water.
Add cold water.
After mixture is cool, pour over the layer of cream cheese.
This salad is pretty and colorful as well as delicious.

title: lady rosemary's pancakes
directions: Sieve flour, salt, soda, cream of tartar and sugar into bowl. Make hollow in center of mixture, crack egg into hollow and gradually add milk.
Stir with wooden spoon from the center, drawing the flour until all is mixed.
Heat skillet, add 1 tablespoon cooking oil.
Cook pancakes.
When finished, butter pancakes; sprinkle with sugar and lemon juice.

title: great batter mix
directions: Mix ingredients just until dry ingredients are mixed.
Do not overmix.
(Mix by hand.)
Heat oil to 375°; batter and deep fry. Great breading for onion rings, veggies and fish.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter and peanut butter.
Add the sugar gradually. Continue beating.
Add eggs. Sift the flour, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture. Chill dough well. Form into walnut size balls.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: party pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese and spices. Cook 10 minutes stirring constant. Add spices and cook 10 more minutes stirring. Drain meat grease. Cook meat until done. Add cheese and cook stirring until cheese melts, about 5 minutes. Cool. Place a mound on each piece of bread laid on cookie sheet. Cool and freeze in plastic bags. When ready to use, thaw and cook about 10 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: harvard beets
directions: Warm beets and drain.
Cook and stir last 4 ingredients.
When clear, add beets and stir to coat beets.
Allow to set 10 minutes before serving.
Reheat if necessary.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook meat.
Stir in all ingredients.
Put in a lined baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese on top.
Cook until cheese is bubbling hot.

title: condensed milk custard(flan de leche condensada)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Caramelize a round 8 x 3-inch aluminum pan without tube by melting 1 cup sugar slowly in the pan to a light gold.
Swirl the pan to coat bottom and sides with caramel. Set on wire rack.
In a saucepan, mix gradually the remaining ingredients; strain.
Pour mixture into the caramelized pan. Place pan over a vessel containing about 1 inch of hot water; bake for about 1 hour, or until set and golden.
Allow to cool on wire rack.
Cover; set in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, turn custard onto a platter.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine; add 3 tablespoons sugar and mix with pretzels. Place in 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Let cool.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar and eggs. Stir in buttermilk. Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and spices; stir into creamed mixture. Stir in oatmeal, and raisins. Drop from tablespoon 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400 degrees for 8 minutes.

title: apple goodie
directions: Mix and put in 9 x 13-inch pan or Pyrex.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut up and fry bacon strips; saute all vegetables.
Fry bread until dried out.
Mix bacon, eggplant and sauteed vegetables. Mix with egg and cheese.
Bake at 300° until brown.

title: crab-artichoke tarts
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl; stir well.
Add chopped bell peppers, artichokes and crabmeat; stir well.
Coat 32 miniature muffin cups with cooking spray.
Gently press 1 wonton wrapper into each muffin cup, allowing ends to extend above edges of cups.
Spoon crabmeat mixture evenly into wonton-wrapper cups; sprinkle with cheese and chives.
Brush edges of wonton wrappers with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until crabmeat mixture is set and edges of wonton wrappers are lightly browned.
Yields 32 appetizers.

title: tea punch
directions: Brew the tea using package directions. Pour into a 1-gallon container. Add the sugar, orange juice concentrate, lemonade concentrate and enough water to fill the container or add other juices such as pear, peach, pineapple or apricot. Stir well. Serve over crushed ice. Garnish with mint sprigs. Yield: 1 gallon.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Make crumbs by placing graham crackers between 2 sheets of waxed paper and roll into crumbs with rolling pin.
Mix crumbs and sugar in bowl.
Add softened butter and combine with the back of fork.
Pat firmly into bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan.

title: tagliatelle with peas and lettuce(low-fat)
directions: Heat the oil and add the onion.
When the onion is soft, add the lettuce and peas.
Cover and cook gently until peas are soft. Do not overcook or they will lose their color.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook the pasta in boiling, salted water.
Drain, reserving a little of the water for the sauce, adding a little of the pasta water if the pasta seems too dry.

title: chicken casserole with rice
directions: Brown chicken in margarine; turn once.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix chicken soup, sour cream, shredded Mozzarella cheese, cooking wine and Parmesan cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350° until chicken is tender.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Serve chicken and sauce over rice.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into balls and put on cookie sheet.
Use a fork to press them down.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: bread surprise
directions: Roll out bread dough to approximately 12 x 18-inch rectangle. Brown beef and sausage together.
Drain and remove all fat. Spread over bread and press down.
Sprinkle onion, pepper and cheese.
Roll up lengthwise and fold end under.

title: baked corn
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Mix dry ingredients together; stir in milk, eggs, and corn. Pour mixture into a well buttered 9x5x3 loaf/casserole dish and dot with butter. Place in oven and bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean. Yield: 4 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Melt oleo and mix with crackers for top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Blend brown sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Stir in molasses.
Add combined dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, beating well.
Spread in a well-greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream, whipped cream or your favorite topping.

title: pasta salad
directions: Drain pineapple (reserve 1/4 cup juice).
Combine pineapple and reserved juice with remaining ingredients.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fellowship chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender with salt.
Remove from broth; set aside to cool.
Remove skin and bones.
Prepare dumplings.
Mix flour and shortening until mealy.
Add milk and stir.
Dough should be very soft.
Let stand a few minutes.
Punch down and pour 1/2 dough at a time to very well floured cutting board. Knead well.
Roll 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in small pieces.
Drop into a 6-quart cooker (about 4 quarts liquid) consisting of broth with margarine and bouillon.
Cook only until done, add chicken and serve hot.

title: super bowl soup
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Using sharp knife, cut off top of rolls. Pull out center, leaving 1/2 inch in bottom and on sides.
Place on baking dish; set aside.
In small saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in garlic.
Using pastry brush, brush inside of each roll with garlic butter.
Bake until crisp, about 10 minutes.
Turn over in 5 minutes.

title: date nut cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients with dates and nuts.
Add beaten egg yolks and vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 250° in tube pan (ungreased) in middle of oven.
Place deep cookie sheet of water on rack below it while baking.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
Cream Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Beat well.
Fold in soda and vinegar which have been mixed together. Bake 30 minutes in a 350°
oven if using 2 round cake pans.
Bake 35 minutes for an oblong pan.

title: endive salad with bacon dressing
directions: Wash the endive and tear into bite-size pieces.
Wrap in a tea towel and refrigerate in a plastic bag until ready to prepare dressing.

title: linda's tuna patties
directions: Spray skillet with Pam.
Combine ingredients into patties. Cook patties; turn often.

title: baked ham sandwiches
directions: Combine first five ingredients, mixing well.
Spread mixture on both sides of buns.
Place one ham slice and one cheese slice on bottom of each bun; cover with top of bun.
Wrap each sandwich in foil and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: sliced pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, onions, peppers, garlic and salt 3 hours in ice water.
Combine sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to boil and pour over pickles that have been packed in jars.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix liquid ingredients.
Stir in brown sugar.
Stir in salt, flour, and nuts.
Spread in a greased and floured 13 X 9 pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and open door and let set for about 10 minutes.

title: butterfinger bars
directions: Cream margarine, sugars and butter flavoring.
Add oatmeal and mix well.
Press into 9 x 13 pan. Bake 12 -15 minutes in 350° oven. Cool.
When cool frost with melted chocolate chips and peanut butter.

title: tuna pie(microwave)
directions: Grease a 9 or 10-inch glass pie plate.	In medium-sized bowl, beat
eggs	just until blended.
Add rice, tuna, onions, melted butter
and
thyme;
stir until blended.
Spoon mixture into pie plate.
Press
with
back of spoon to pack slightly. Cover loosely with
waxed
paper.
Microwave
on High 7 to 10 minutes, until mixture
is set, rotating plate 1/4 turn once. Sprinkle top
with cheese; let stand covered 3 minutes, until cheese melts.
Arrange tomato
wedges
around
edge.
Makes 6 servings; 257 calories per serving.

title: ham loaf
directions: Bake in large loaf pan or two smaller ones at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown on top.
Freezes well!

title: easy taco bake
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with baking spray.
Brown ground chuck and onion in frying pan; drain off fat.
Press biscuits into bottom and sides of pan, pinching together to form crust.
Sprinkle with meat mixture, then sprinkle with taco seasoning to taste, then sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes, until browned.
Serve with salsa, if desired.

title: 5 cup fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients in order and chill for a few hours before serving.

title: gourmet chocolate cheesecake
directions: Mix ingredients and press onto bottom and up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: john's festive casserole
directions: Crumble and brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Spread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drain green beans and layer on top. Drain carrots and layer next.
By spoonfuls, drop on 1 can tomato soup.
Spread mashed potatoes on top.
Drop by spoonfuls, second can of soup on top of potatoes.
Spread cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Serves 10.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Crumble salmon with liquid in mixing
bowl;
add
bread (crumbled) and onion.
Let salmon, bread and onion set for 1/2 hour.
Add eggs and Bisquick.
Mix ingredients
and
drop	by spoonfuls into hot oil in frypan.

title: fettucini
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Dissolve bouillon cube in 1 tablespoon hot water.
Add shrimp 1 minute before noodles are done.
Drain noodles and shrimp and return to pan.
Add dissolved bouillon.
Alternately add cheese and cream or half and half, making sure cheese is melted before adding more liquid.
(If it is not thin enough, milk may be used.)
Add garlic powder to taste.

title: cheese ballssocorro, new mexico
directions: Mix all ingredients together including 1/2 cup nuts and the rest to roll ball in.

title: microwave red snapper delight
directions: Cut green onions into 2-inch pieces.
Cut carrots and red peppers into thin strips.
Slice celery.
Cut tail of fish and place in 19 x 9-inch baking dish.
Brush with butter.
Arrange vegetables around fish.
In bowl cook garlic and oil on High for 1 1/2 minutes until garlic is golden.
Discard garlic.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over fish and vegetables.
Cook covered on High for 12 to 14 minutes, just until outer edges of fish are opaque, removing lid and stirring vegetables 1/2 way through baking process.
Garnish with kiwi fruit slices and almonds.
Makes 4 servings.

title: french toast
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl, except powdered sugar and bread.
Dip 1 slice of bread into mixture and place onto griddle (continue this until griddle is full).
Brown evenly on both sides.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar on top and serve.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix well.
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 60 to 90 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes in pan, then glaze.

title: baked alaskan salmon
directions: Wash and dry salmon.
Split the fish open; leave skin intact. In a bowl, combine bread, onion, parsley, salt, pepper and sage; mix well.
Add the butter and broth and mix.
Stuff the fish with the mixture carefully.
Do not pack down or filling will become heavy; fasten the edges with skewers or thread.
Place on buttered baking dish; arrange
bacon across the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: birthday cookie
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs.
Add the dry ingredients, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Bake in greased 14 1/2 x 5/8-inch round pizza pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Makes 2 loaves or 18 muffins.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: venison sausage skillet
directions: *May substitute package of frozen sliced carrots.

title: gumbo
directions: In large dutch oven or heavy pot make roux using oil and flour, brown to deep brown over medium heat, be careful not to burn.
More oil may be added if necessary. In large pot, chop onions, bell pepper and celery, saute until onion is clear.
Add chicken broth, roux, tomatoes, garlic, salt, pepper and 1 qt water.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add okra and shrimp, simmer 20 minutes more, until okra is done.
Add crab meat and after 5 minutes, 1/3 bottle of File. Let cool and reheat before serving. You may need to add additional water.

title: cream cheese balls(appetizer)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Form a ball.
Roll in chopped parsley.
Serve with fancy crackers or celery.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet.
Cook well done.
Set aside. Saute onion, green pepper and celery in 1/2 stick margarine.
Add 5 cups hot water.
When this is boiling, pour in dry soup mix. Add rice and cook until done and water is absorbed.

title: venus de milo soup
directions: Saute onion.
Add ground beef and saute until red disappears. Transfer to large pan and add rest of ingredients.
Simmer covered for 15 minutes.

title: dietetic spice cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until soft.
Drain.
Add applesauce or pineapple and eggs.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes.

title: salmon stuffed eggs
directions: Shell eggs; carefully cut into halves lengthwise.
Take out yolks.
Rub salmon, anchovy and egg yolks through a sieve or whirl in blender.
Cream butter; add salmon mixture, Worcestershire and seasoning to taste.
Mix well.
Stuff into whites (the mixture). Makes 20 delicious and different salmon stuffed eggs.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients well together.
Drop the resultant batter into a buttered pan by teaspoonfuls.
Bake in a moderate oven and be proud of the result.

title: sweet cinnamon rolls
directions: Pour scalded milk over sugar, salt and lard.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add to first mixture.
Beat eggs and mix.
Add flour (more may be added).
Should be a little sticky yet.
Let rise once, then roll out and spread with butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and cut.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sugar and blend well.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel apples and place in a baking pan.
Combine sugar, flour and margarine for topping.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top of apples and flour, sugar and margarine for topping.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook onion in butter until soft.
Cook broccoli and cheese according to directions on package.
Mix Jiffy cornbread mix, eggs, onion, butter, cheese and Green Giant broccoli and cheese. Pour into heated and greased cast-iron skillet and bake about 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: Cream butter, add confectioners sugar, cocoa, egg yolks and salt.
Cream until thoroughly blended.
Blend in vanilla and milk. Cream until desired spreading consistency.
This recipe makes enough frosting for a 2 layer 8 or 9-inch cake.

title: seafood medley
directions: Melt butter. Add celery, onion and garlic; saute. Add shrimp and crabmeat. Cook linguine; drain. Add whipping cream. Mix with seafood mixture. Salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle each serving with Parmesan cheese.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Mix peppers, sugar and vinegar.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add color and Certo.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour in small hot jars and seal.

title: angel cake with strawberry filling
directions: Mix, bake and cool cake.
Partially thaw strawberries.
Drain, reserving 3/4 cup juice from fruit.
Prepare whipped topping. Combine with fruit, all but 5 or 6 for garnish.
Slice cake into 3 layers.
Spread mixture between layers.

title: protein raisin-gem cookies
directions: Sift flour, soy flour, baking soda and salt onto wax paper. Beat diet margarine, brown sugar, sugar substitute, vanilla and egg until well blended.
Add sifted dry ingredients to margarine mixture; mix well.
Stir in raisins.

title: sisters "tacky casserole"
directions: *Use the same size oz. can of chili and tamales.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Blend together in a blender carrots and milk.
Mix rest of ingredients together including blender mixture and place in buttered casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: corned beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until tender; drain well.
Arrange alternate layers of cabbage and corned beef in a shallow 2-quart casserole. Combine soup, milk, onion, mustard and salt.
Pour mixture over corned beef and cabbage.
Toss bread cubes in butter.
Arrange around edge of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Arrange cheese over center of casserole.
Bake 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: vanilla or amaretto custard sauce
directions: In the top of a double boiler over simmering water, heat cream until hot but not boiling. Beat egg yolks well in a small bowl. Combine a small amount of the hot cream with the egg yolks and then pour the egg mixture back into the cream. Stir in the sugar. Cook and stir custard until it is thick enough to coat the back of a spoon. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Chill.

title: egg-milk-butterless cake
directions: Boil sugar, lard, raisins, water, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt for 3 minutes.
(Boil 3 minutes after it starts to boil.) Take off the stove and let cool (real cold).
Then stir in flour, baking powder and soda.
Bake in a slow oven for 1 hour at 300° or until done.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; place between paper towels and squeeze out water.
Mix all ingredients and serve with pumpernickel bread or crackers.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In large saucepan, combine margarine, cocoa, sugar and milk, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and vanilla. Stir until peanut butter melts, then add approximately 3 cups oats. If you used more peanut butter, you may want to add just a few more oats.

title: lemonade with sherbet
directions: Place lemonade in glass within 2 inches of top of glass and fill within 1 1/2 inches of top of glass with ice.
Add lemon sherbet.
Garnish with slice of lemon on side of glass.
Place maraschino cherry and sprig of fresh mint on top of sherbet.
Serve with a straw and a soda spoon.
Yield:
1 serving.

title: frozen desserts
directions: Mix all together until well blended.
Put in plastic container with lid. Freeze a couple of hours. Serve in dishes.

title: corn relish
directions: Cook corn in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Cut from cob. Measure 8 cups.
Combine corn with remaining ingredients and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Bring to a boil, pack in hot, sterilized jars.
Seal.
Process 15 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yield: About 6 pints.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and lined loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: country captain chicken
directions: Dredge chicken in seasoned flour; fry until brown.
Remove chicken; keep warm.
Cook onions, peppers and garlic in remaining pan drippings until tender.
Stir in curry powder, salt, pepper, thyme, tomatoes and parsley; heat well.
Place chicken in a large casserole.
Stir almonds and raisins into sauce and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until done.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together corn, flour, sugar and salt.
Combine milk, eggs and butter; add to corn mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir every 10 minutes for first 30 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredient sin a 2-quart bowl.
Mix in a saucepan, the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring well.
Turn off heat and allow to cool.
When cool, pour over the vegetables, mixing well.
Cover and set in refrigerator until cold.
This will keep a week to 10 days.

title: peppy potatoes
directions: Mix tomatoes, water and oregano in a 2-quart ovenware casserole dish.
Heat to boiling, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in seasoning mix and potatoes.
Cook for 5 minutes at medium heat. Stir.
Place cheese and pepperoni on top.
Turn oven to 350° and cook for an additional 10 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender and cheese is melted.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding and beat with wire whisk, 1 to 2 minutes (mixture will be thick). Stir in pumpkin and spices with wire whisk; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.

title: texas rice casserole
directions: Use a 2-quart baking dish and layer:

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Crumble sausage and fry until browned. Pour off all excess grease. Add other ingredients, mixing well. Put in baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until browned on top.

title: layered salad
directions: In a bowl, layer first 8 ingredients in the order given. Chill for 24 hours.
When ready to serve, salt to taste.
Toss and top with Parmesan cheese.
Must be made a day before serving.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.
While still hot, spread with 1 cup chocolate chips.
Put back into oven to melt chips.
When cool, spread with 1/2 cup powdered sugar, 1/4 cup peanut butter and 2 to 3 tablespoons milk.

title: pumpkin loaves
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients with a fork.
Then add pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Blend and divide into two 9 x 5-inch greased loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool and remove from pans.

title: best pulled pork
directions: Salt and pepper roast very well. Place in a crock-pot. Cover with water and onion. Place on medium heat and cook overnight. When roast is done, shred meat. Do not chop! Cover completely with the wildfire sauce. Place this in crock-pot on low. Serve on a fresh roll or bun, piled high and covered with Country Cole Slaw (found in salad section).

title: pork barbecue
directions: Remove excess fat from roast.
Fit roast into crock pot. Cover meat with beer or water, vinegar and onion to taste.
Add peppers.
Cook on low 10 to 12 hours, until meat is falling off the bone.
Drain liquid.
Separate meat from fat.
Return lean meat to crock pot.
Add sauce to meat and cook another 2 to 4 hours.

title: seafood pasta
directions: Saute onion, peppers, add mushrooms and seafood, tomatoes. Cook covered until shrimp is done.
Mix with cooked fettucini. Serves in pasta bowls topped with fresh parmesan or romano cheese.

title: spicy rice dish
directions: Mix rice and sour cream.
Put 1/2 of rice mixture in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle on Cheddar cheese and chili peppers.
Dot with butter.
Layer rest of rice mixture on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Dot with butter.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Don't let it dry out.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour loaf pans.
Combine dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, combine beaten eggs, strawberries (include juice) and oil.
Pour liquid into a "well" made in the center of the dry ingredients.
Mix with hands.
Will make 3 large loaf pans (or use 16 mini loaf pans).
Bake 45 to 60 minutes. (Test for doneness after 1 hour.)

title: company cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine graham cracker crumbs, walnuts and butter.
Press on bottom and 2/3 up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat smooth eggs, softened cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and almond extract.
Blend in sour cream.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 375° about 35 minutes or just until set.
Cool.
Chill 4 to 5 hours before serving.
Filling will be soft.

title: crustless green chile quiche
directions: Whip the eggs in a mixing bowl until fluffy.
Whisk in the melted butter, flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in the cottage cheese, chilies, black pepper and half the Mozzarella.
Place the mixture in a greased 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Top with the remaining cheese.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes. Then reduce the temperature to 350° and continue to bake for 35 to 40 minutes, or until the eggs are set and the top is lightly browned.
Allow to cool a bit and cut into squares.

title: danish puff coffee cake
directions: Measure first cup of flour into bowl.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons water and mix with fork.
Round into ball and divide in half.
Pat each piece on large cookie sheet into 2 long 12 x 3-inch strips.
Strips should be 3-inches apart on ungreased sheet.
Mix second amount of butter and water.
Bring to rolling boil.
Add almond flavoring and remove from heat.
Stir in flour immediately to keep it from lumping.
When smooth and thick, add 1 egg at a time, beating until smooth.
Divide in half and spread 1/2 evenly over each strip of pastry.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes until crisp and browned.
Frost with powdered sugar icing and chopped nuts.

title: french pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in unbaked pie shell for 1 hour at 350°.

title: janet's praline graham squares
directions: Line cookie pan with edge, with graham crackers broken in half, then quarters.
Boil together butter and sugar for 2 minutes.
Add nuts and vanilla; mix well and spoon (and pour) over crackers, covering evenly.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until surface is bubbling all over (makes praline effect).
While still warm, cut rectangles in 1/2 to make squares.
Wonderful!

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Precook vegetable mixture and potatoes. In saucepan, cook onion and celery in butter or margarine until tender.
Add pepper and thyme to taste.
Add soups milk and stir until smooth.

title: "lite" jambalaya
directions: In a heavy pan, saute chicken cubes, butter, onions and garlic until chicken is thoroughly cooked.
Add sausage, salt, pepper, nutmeg and cloves and simmer on low heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth and water and bring to a boil.
Stir in rice; lower heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until rice is tender and most of the liquid is absorbed.
Stir in shrimp and let them get hot.
Pour into serving dish with cayenne pepper.
Serve hot!

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Press firmly in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: coconut chews
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, nuts, cherries and lemon peel.
Mix. Whip egg white and salt until stiff.
Fold in coconut mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheets about 2 inches apart.
Bake about 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hungarian meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in greased loaf pan or casserole.
Bake one hour at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes before slicing.
Serve with catsup or tomatoes.

title: strawberry delight salad
directions: Just pour everything in a bowl and stir until thoroughly mixed, then refrigerate for about an hour or freeze depending on which firmness you prefer.

title: bride and angel salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Set aside to cool (do not jell). Mix cheese, sugar and mayonnaise.
Add marshmallows, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Gently stir in gelatin mixture until well blended.
Let set until firm.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; blend thoroughly. Pour into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread dry cake mix over batter in pan. Pour butter evenly over cake mix; sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool; cut in squares.

title: meat loaf
directions: Tear bread slices into bits and cover with 1 cup milk then mix all the ingredients together and spread in an ungreased loaf pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.
Glaze top with 1/4 cup ketchup and 2 tablespoons corn syrup.

title: french chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, water and rice well in casserole.
Place cut up chicken on top.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top; cover tightly. Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Start with vanilla wafers, then strawberries, last add Cool Whip.
Layer like this until you fill your bowl.
Let set in refrigerator 2 or 3 hours.

title: stew in roaster
directions: Note:
You can use peas, beans or mushrooms.

title: 8-minute fruity pie
directions: *Can use fresh berries or bananas. Can use any canned fruit, drained (1 cup).

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix egg and sugar together.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Mix everything together.
Put into 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: fancy easy coffeecake
directions: Dip each biscuit in butter and sugar.
Lay in a circle in a Bundt pan.
Stagger the next circle of biscuit on top to fill empty spaces.
You add nuts, cinnamon and raisins.
Use Bundt pan and bake at 375° until brown.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place
in
ovenproof	casserole dish. Top with cracker crumbs and shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli, rice and cheese
directions: Cook both rice and broccoli; mix together.
Add and mix chicken soup, butter, Cheez Whiz, milk and onion.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, covered.
Take cover off the last 5 minutes.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water.
Add melted shortening. Stir in dry ingredients.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Roll out, cut and place in greased pan.
Grease top with melted oleo or butter.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake in a 400° oven.

title: carol's red stroganoff
directions: Brown steak with onion, basil and salts.
Add the tomato and cream of mushroom soups.
Add mushrooms and cook on low-medium heat for 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.
Just before serving, add sour cream.
Serve over mashed potatoes or rice.

title: coconut candy balls
directions: Bring syrup to a rolling boil.
Remove from stove and add coconut.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Dampen hands and roll into balls. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Use your own judgment as to how much paraffin you want.
Dip coconut balls into chocolate.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Peel bananas; squeeze lemon juice over bananas. Wrap them in plastic bag and freeze until solid.
Chill 4 champagne glasses or bowls.
Cut bananas into small slices.
Blend in food processor with vanilla extract and milk.
Blend until very smooth; if mixture becomes too thick, add more milk.
Pour into chilled glasses or bowls.
Return to freezer, not longer than 2 hours. Garnish and serve with strawberries, kiwi slices or other fresh fruit.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Mix sour cream with mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Mix avocado with onion.
Layer bean dip, sour cream mixture and remaining ingredients in order given in a 2 quart cake pan. Refrigerate.
Serve chilled with taco chips.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch or larger casserole dish with Pam. Combine soup and sour cream. Layer half of the chicken, half of the soup mixture and all of the broccoli, as the center layer. Continue to layer with chicken and soup mixture.
Top with Ritz crackers, mixed with melted margarine.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pie crusts(4 singles)
directions: Blend first four ingredients with pastry blender.
Add egg. Add water and vinegar; pour over flour mixture and stir with fork. Divide into 4 parts and freeze for future use.

title: spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach into pieces.
Add onion, cheese, honey and Italian dressing to taste.

title: brownies
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, melt chocolate and butter or margarine. Remove from heat.
(Mix the rest of the ingredients in by hand.) Add sugar and mix well.
Add each egg, one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and mix well.
Add pecans.
Spray just the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan with Pam. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes clean.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet with celery, pepper and onion.
Add rice to mixture.
Pour into Pyrex dish.
Combine soup according to package directions.
Pour over sausage and rice mixture.

title: crunchy chicken
directions: Roll each piece of cut up chicken in butter, then in corn flakes.
Place in baking pan.
Pour any remaining butter over chicken, then sprinkle with dry onion soup.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable beef and biscuit casserole
directions: Cook beef until browned; drain off fat.
Stir in soups, water, mixed vegetables and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Remove dish from oven; stir and arrange biscuits on hot beef mixture.
Top with cheese. Bake 10 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt margarine in 12 x 7 1/2-inch casserole dish.
Cube chicken and place in margarine.
Pour soup mixture over.
Add Veg-All and cheese.
Add milk to flour stirring until smooth. Pour flour mixture over ingredients (this makes a crust).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll in pecans.
Roll into a ball. Chill overnight before serving.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil together in large mixer bowl.
Mix instant pudding in cake mix.
Then add to egg mixture alternately with water, mixing well.
Beat 2 minutes or until completely mixed. Fold in poppy seed.

title: breakfast bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in loaf pan at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: chinese rice
directions: Cook rice in hot oil over medium heat until golden brown.
Add salt, water, bouillon cube and soy sauce.
Add onion, celery and pepper.
Cover tightly and simmer 10 minutes.
(It may be necessary to add a little more water.)

title: strawberry banana pie
directions: In large bowl, combine filling and bananas.
Spoon into pie crust.
Spread whipped topping over pie.
Chill several hours.

title: aunt marian's christmas banana bread with pecans
directions: Mash bananas with fork.
Blend in sugar, salt and beaten egg. Melt butter and stir into banana mixture. Dissolve soda in water and add with sifted flour.
Mix.
Add 1/4 cup broken nutmeats and bake in greased loaf pan for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Frost with thin vanilla icing.
Sprinkle with red and green crystallized sugar and decorate with pecans.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: cowboy casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add soups and sauce.
Layer in casserole dish, beginning with chips, meat and cheese.
Top with chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: german potato salad with sour cream(makes 4 servings)
directions: Slice potatoes while still warm.
If new potatoes are used, slice in their jackets.
Old potatoes should be peeled.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and sweetened condensed milk.
Add fresh lemon juice (the acid in the lemon juice "cooks" the eggs).
Pour into pie crust.

title: fig, peach and raspberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Adjust oven rack to middle level. Remove small stem from each fig; cut figs into quarters.
Mix figs with remaining fruit, 1/4 cup sugar and water.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Cut 2 tablespoons butter into small pieces and place over top evenly; set aside.

title: edible peanut butter play doh
directions: Mix peanut butter and corn syrup.
Add dry milk and powdered sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Store in an airtight container until ready to use.

title: ziti bake
directions: Prepare ziti as label directs. Brown hamburg. Drain. Add Ricotta and Parmesan cheese, parsley, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 of sauce. Mix well.
Add ziti.
Toss gently and coat well.
Spoon mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Pour remaining sauce over mixture and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Add eggs, oil and pumpkin. Beat 1 minute (or more). Pour in greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots; drain.
Combine with onion and pepper in large bowl.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Pour over carrots in bowl.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight; drain.
Return any leftover vegetables to marinate; keep refrigerated.
Makes 5 cups.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix butter, 1 egg and cake mix together.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Beat cream cheese, 2 eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: 5 layer taco dip
directions: Cook hamburger and taco mix according to directions on envelope.
Drain fat.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine Bisquick, milk and eggs in one bowl.
Chop up onion, green pepper and broccoli.
Shred Cheddar cheese and put it separate to the side.
Grease a pie plate with butter.
Add in broccoli, onion and green pepper to pie plate. Pour the liquid mixture over the ingredients.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese, garlic salt and pepper.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, checking it towards the end, in case it browns.
Let cool and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana cake icing
directions: Place milk and sugar in heavy saucepan.
Cook on high, continually stirring until it begins to boil.
Lower to medium or low heat and continue to cook for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add milk, egg yolks and butter.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add vanilla.
Put into browned pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown in 375° oven.

title: banana pie
directions: Prepare pie shell as directed.
Prepare pudding as directed. Add bananas.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients. Spoon into small ovenproof pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling, salted water.
Reserve liquid. Melt butter; add onion until soft.
Blend in flour and broth.
Cook until boiling.
Stir in 1 cup liquid from cooked cauliflower.
Add cream, Worcestershire sauce, salt, cauliflower and cheese.

title: hot sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and cook over low heat for 1 hour; stir occasionally.

title: raisin bars
directions: Bring the water and raisins to a boil; remove from heat and add brown sugar and oil or margarine.
Cool mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet (large).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: dutch oven beef enchiladas
directions: Brown ground
beef,
onions,
pepper,
onion
salt
and garlic powder in a 14-inch Dutch oven.
When done, remove meat from
oven and
drain
off drippings.
Put a little enchilada sauce in the bottom of the Dutch oven.
Layer 6 tortillas, 1/3 of the
meat mixture, 1/4 of the sauce and 1/4 of the cheese. Repeat
layers twice, ending with remaining sauce and cheese. Cook, covered, with
coals on the top and 14 coals on the bottom for 20 minutes or until bubbling.	Garnish with chopped green onions and serve.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease an 8-inch square pan. Blend flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour, cinnamon, salt, baking powder and dry milk powder. Mix melted shortening, eggs and oatmeal and mix well; add water and vanilla.
Add 1/2 flour mixture; then currants and nuts, then add rest of flour.
Drop on greased baking sheet and bake at 400° about 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: baked custard
directions: Whisk the eggs, milk, sugar and salt.
Pour into 4 ungreased 8 ounce custard cups.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; pour hot water in pan to a depth of 2-inches.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.
Remove cups to a wire rack to cool.
Serve warm or chilled.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: yummy potato rounds
directions: Preheat broiler with rack 4 to 6 inches below element.

Place potato slices in single layer on lightly oiled baking sheets. Sprinkle slices with small amounts of Vege-sal and garlic powder. Sprinkle with slightly larger amounts of onion powder and paprika. Place under broiler for about 5 minutes or until golden.
Remove from oven; turn slices over and sprinkle again with same seasoning.
Return to broiler for about 5 minutes until golden. Enjoy.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix and divide into 3 equal cake pans.
Bake until done.
While cake is baking, heat in a saucepan 1 pint sour cream.
Fill the sour cream container with sugar and pour into sour cream.
Add chopped nuts.
Cook until it boils and boil for a few minutes.
Place sour cream mixture in refrigerator and cool.
When cake is cooled, layer cake, mixture, cake, mixture, cake and mixture.
Place whole nuts on top to decorate.

title: wagon wheel sausage pie
directions: Cook sausage until very light brown; drain.
Generously grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/4-inch), spread potatoes in pie plate.
Mix onions, 2 tablespoons milk, salt, pepper and cream cheese; spread over potatoes.
Beat baking mix with 1/3 cup milk and the eggs with wire whisk or hand beater until almost smooth, about 1 minute; pour around sausages.
Bake, uncovered, until edge is light brown and center is set, 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
tags: Hormel little sizzlers skinless pork sausage

title: broiled catfish fillets
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, bring onion, mustard, salt, pepper, Worcestershire, soy sauce and lemon juice to a boil; remove from heat.
Place catfish fillets on a foil-lined cookie sheet; cover with sauce and sprinkle with paprika.
Broil 7 inches from heat at 450° for about 20 minutes.

title: corn mush
directions: Bring water to a boil, then mix in rest of the ingredients, stirring with a wire whisk.
Boil 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan or loaf pan.
Place in refrigerator to cool completely. Slice in thin pieces and fry in hot oil until golden brown on both sides. Good with apple butter or syrup.

title: cheesecake
directions: Put Melba toast and Equal in blender to crumble.
Spread in bottom of 8-inch square pan, reserving a little to sprinkle on top.
Put remaining ingredients in blender and blend until required consistency.
Spread over Melba crumbs and top with reserved crumbs.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Before serving, divide into 6 equal portions.

title: grace's tangy vegetable salad
directions: Cut cauliflower into florets and combine with stuffed olives, diced avocado and diced tomatoes.
Line salad boil with lettuce and add ingredients combined with either dressing or the Bleu cheese.
Refrigerate for a short time before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: italian garlic toast
directions: In a small bowl combine butter, cheese, garlic and oregano. Brush onto the cut surfaces of the bread.
Broil about 4 inches from the heat until lightly toasted.

title: marinated cold vegetable salad
directions: Drain corn, peas and lima beans.
Chop fine the pepper, celery and onion.
Mix these together.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Saute onions, carrots and celery in melted butter.
Add flour and cornstarch; cook until bubbly.
Add stock and milk; make a smooth sauce.
Add seasonings and cheese; heat thoroughly.
Add parsley for a few minutes before serving.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Grease baking sheet heavily with margarine.
Combine sugar, corn syrup and salt in 3-quart dish.
Stir in peanuts. Microwave on high until light brown, about 8 to 10 minutes; stir 2 times. Stir in remaining ingredients until light and foamy.
Quickly spread on greased baking sheet.
Spread thin.

title: state senate bean soup
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight.
Add onions, garlic, parsley, thyme, bay leaf and ham bone.
Cover.
Cook slowly until tender. Remove ham bone, meat and bay leaf.
Remove 2 cups beans with a little liquid.
Puree and return to pot with 1 cup water.
Cut ham into small pieces and return to soup pot.
Serve hot with corn bread.

title: apple-stuffed pork chops
directions: In a skillet, saute onion in butter until tender.
Remove from the heat.
Add bread, apples, celery, parsley and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cut a large pocket in the side of each pork chop; sprinkle inside and outside with pepper and remaining salt.
Spoon stuffing loosely into pockets.
In a large skillet, brown the chops on both sides in oil.
Place in an ungreased large baking pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer or until meat juices run clear.
Make gravy from pan juices, if desired.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: easy pumpkin pudding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; blend well with electric mixer at medium speed.
Beat for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 55 minutes or until cake test done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then invert onto serving plate.
Sprinkle with powder sugar before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: baked chicken in sour cream(serves 6 to 10)
directions: Remove all cuts of bone and place chicken in shallow dish. Mix sour cream and seasoning together and pour over chicken. Turn each piece to coat well. Refrigerate overnight. Coat each piece with bread crumbs and place in one layer in baking dish. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 1/2 hours. Uncover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: triple chocolate brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch pie plate.
In a small mixing bowl, beat eggs; blend in sugar and butter.
In separate bowl, stir together flour, cocoa and salt; add to beaten mixture, beating until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla. Bake 35 minutes.

title: raspberry cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O gelatin in 2 cups hot water.
Stir in cranberry sauce, undrained pineapple and 7-Up.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in celery and nuts.
Chill until set.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, except poppy seed.
Blend well with a beater.
Add poppy seed.
Pour in a covered quart container and refrigerate.
Yields 1 quart.

title: nappa salad
directions: Break dry noodles in bowl and sprinkle with several drops of sesame oil.
Mix together cabbage, snow peas, green onions, sesame seed and slivered almonds.

title: fried apples
directions: Chop bacon into small pieces and fry until crisp.
Wash and slice apples thin.
Add to bacon.
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Cook over low heat until done.
Stir often.
The apples will be very soft when done.

title: pineapple sherbet drink
directions: Peel and slice pineapple and chop coarsely. Place in a container. Make a syrup with the sugar and 1 pint of water. Pour it boiling over the pineapple; add lime juice. Stir all together and let stand covered for a couple of hours. Add the remainder of the water, strain into another container, and just before serving add a few pieces of ice to each cup or glass of punch.

title: gazpacho
directions: In a blender, mix tomatoes, olive oil, vinegar, garlic powder and toasted bread.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve well chilled.

title: pralines and cream
directions: Mix oatmeal, brown sugar, margarine, pecans and flour in a large pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°, stirring mixture every 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Divide crumbs in half, putting half on the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1 jar of topping over.
Layer the softened ice cream next, then the other jar of topping.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze until needed.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Combine red pepper, soup and sour cream.
Stir in chicken. Spoon into casserole dish.
Mix butter, cracker crumbs and poppy seed.
Put this on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes or until brown on top and bubbly.

title: quick apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples in pie pan; sprinkle with cinnamon, 1 teaspoon sugar and butter.
Sift 1 cup sugar (1/2 cup if sweet apples), baking powder, flour and salt.
Work in egg until mixture is crumbly and cover apples.
Melt 1/2 stick of margarine and pour over apples.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Watch; if pie gets too brown, turn oven back.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add flour and eggs, mixing well. Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick tests done.

title: naturally sweet sky-high apple pie
directions: Combine apples, juice and raisins in a heavy pot over low heat.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring gently.
Remove mixture from pot and stir in all other pie ingredients.
Fill the bottom pie crust with mixture, piling it very, very high.
It will sink in baking.
Pour in small amount of the liquid remaining in the pot. Place top crust on pie; seal edges well.
Prick with fork or paring knife to make steam holes.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 375° or until filling is tender and crust is done (slightly browned). If crust overbrowns too early, place slitted foil over pie to complete baking.
Cool for 1 hour before slicing.

title: mama's hickory nut cake
directions: *Note:	Don't
worry
about
chopping them, by the time you get them out of the hull, they're in bits already!

title: sweetened chex mix
directions: Put cereal and nuts on a cookie sheet.
Boil margarine and brown sugar for 2 minutes.
Drizzle over cereal mix.
Bake 8 minutes at 325°.
Stir and bake 8 minutes more.
Cool and put in container.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix all and let set for 2 to 3 hours and put in freezer.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Place one vanilla wafer on bottom of cupcake paper and put cream cheese mixture (first 4 items mixed together) on the wafer. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Place pie filling on top and cool. Makes 2 dozen.

title: western bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans and place in baking dish.
Cook onions in bacon drippings until done.
Add soup to onions and pour over beans.
Sprinkle pecans and grated cheese over top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Boil and dice chicken breasts, cool.
Mix mayonnaise with lemon juice, curry and soya sauce.
Mix with rest of ingredients; chill and top with noodles.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender; mix well.
Grease a 10-inch pie pan with oleo and sprinkle coconut on bottom of pan. Pour blended mix into pie pan.
Place in cold oven.
Turn on oven to 325° and bake 40 to 55 minutes or until firm in middle.
You won't believe this!

title: hershey pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add melted candy bars and buttermilk; mix well.
Combine flour, salt and soda; add to chocolate mixture, mixing well.
Add pecans, chocolate syrup and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until done.

title: swiss chicken bake
directions: Place chicken breasts in bottom of casserole dish.
Place Swiss cheese slice atop each breast.
Dilute soup with 1/4 cup water and mix well.
Pour over cheese.
Saute bread stuffing crumbs with butter and spread over top.
Cover dish tightly with aluminum foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake again for 15 minutes or until crumbs crisp up.
Moist and flavorful!

title: potato candy
directions: You also need wax paper.

title: fruity orange punch
directions: Mix well and add 1-quart orange sherbet.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and shred.
In saucepan over low heat combine cheese and 1/4 cup butter.
Stir occasionally until almost melted. Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Add to potatoes in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Set dish in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. After 30 minutes, inserted spoon at edge of pudding and stir from bottom.
Continue baking until knife inserted near center of pudding comes out clean.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: reuben casserole
directions: *Or use enough corned beef, cooked and shredded to cover sauerkraut and dressing mixture in pan.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together in skillet and heat, then pour over sausage balls.

title: clam sauce
directions: Mince or chop garlic cloves. Saute in olive oil.
Add dried parsley at last minute of sauteing.
Add water, clams, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 5 or 6 minutes.
Pour over cooked spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and red pepper.
Serves 2 people generously.
Doesn't look real appetizing but it's delicious.
Serve with garlic bread and a salad.

title: seafood vegetable spread
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sour cream and dip mix.
On serving plate, spread cheese mixture into circle. Chill at least 1 hour.
Just before serving, top with cocktail sauce, then crabmeat.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add celery and onion, then add rest of ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole and bake for 1 1/2 hours or more in 350° oven.

title: fettuccine chicken casserole
directions: Cook fettuccine in boiling salted water until just tender, following package directions.
Drain.
Toss with 3 tablespoons of butter, Parmesan cheese, cream, chicken, Fontina cheese, nutmeg, salt and pepper.

title: cajun sweet hot pickles
directions: Drain juice off pickles and discard.
Slice pickles into thick slices.
Layer pickles, sugar, pepper, cinnamon and garlic in 4 to 6 layers back in jar.
(Use a potato masher to push them down; they will all fit back in.)
Replace lid.
Seal tightly.
Turn upside down and leave 12 hours; turn up and down every 12 hours for 6 days.
Store in refrigerator.
They will make their own juice; don't add any liquid.

title: chelsea's kid candy
directions: This is healthy snack and a hands-on project.
Younger kids like to mix on dinner plate or wax paper.
Dump peanut butter in middle.
Dump honey in middle of that.
Dump on raisins.
Sprinkle generously with powdered milk, then start to knead and play and knead, adding powdered milk until it's smooth and not sticky.
Eat as is or shape and eat.

title: tootsie's marinara sauce
directions: You can use fresh tomatoes; just put in blender and puree. In a 2-quart saucepan, saute onion, garlic and mushrooms in oil until tender, but not brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer 25 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
If you want a meat sauce, just add meatballs, sausage, etc.

title: lemon-apricot cake
directions: Beat eggs; add cake mix, oil, nectar and extract.
Pour in stem cake pan; bake 55 minutes at 325°.
Cool 10 minutes; turn out and stick cake with ice pick a number of times to allow icing to penetrate cake.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain salmon and remove skin and bones.
Flake salmon and combine with all ingredients except pecans and parsley.
Chill several hours.
Roll into ball.
Roll in nuts and parsley.
Serve surrounded by crackers.

title: brandied fruit starter
directions: Mix well, gently again. Can eat 1 hour later. Serve on pound cake or vanilla ice cream.

title: caraway cabbage wedges
directions: Discard tough outer leaves from cabbage.
Cut cabbage into 4 wedges; cut cores from wedges, leaving just enough to retain shape.
In 12 x 8-inch baking dish, cook cabbage wedges and 1/4 cup water covered on high 12 to 14 minutes until tender, rearranging cabbage halfway through cooking.
Let stand for 5 minutes; drain.
In 1-cup glass measure, cook margarine or butter and caraway seed 45 seconds to 1 minute until melted.
Stir in lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over cabbage.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Combine the chicken, both soups and tomatoes; mix well.
Layer half the crumbled Doritos, 1/2 of the chicken mixture and 1/2 of the taco cheese.
Repeat.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients all together into large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in meat balls.
Turn down to low.
Cook about 40 minutes, covered.
Stir every now and then.
After 40 minutes, add about 30 prunes.
Cover and cook about another 30 minutes.
Serves about 18 to 20.

title: fruit and chicken salad
directions: Combine mayo and mustard.
In a large bowl, combine other ingredients except noodles.
Mix in mayo/mustard sauce.
Serve on a leaf of lettuce and top with noodles.

title: chinese pie
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar and vinegar.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add pecans, raisins, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie crust shell.
Bake for 40 minutes in 325° oven.

title: easy strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake in sheet cake pan.
Mix jello and water.
Punch holes in cake.
Pour jello over cake while hot.
Chill.
Layer with berries.
Mix pudding by directions.
Spread over berries.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Clean shrimp and put into a bowl.
Crush garlic; stir into shrimp and chill together for several hours.
Put shrimp into heated large pot or wok; pour olive oil over shrimp and quickly stir until shrimp begins to cook.
Add tomatoes and oregano; stir until mixture bubbles.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice or pasta.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry minute cream pie
directions: Place strawberries in large saucepan.
Break up with fork and bring to a boil.
Add Jell-O and stir until it dissolves.
Add ice cream to mixture and stir until melted.
Place in refrigerator until partially set (mixture should mound slightly when dropped from spoon).
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill until completely set.
Garnish before serving.

title: traditional cornbread dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly grease baking dish.
Melt butter in skillet; saute celery and onion until tender.
In large mixing bowl, combine cornbread, bread, celery, onion, pepper and sage.
Stir broth and eggs into mixture; blend well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spicy chicken skewers
directions: Coat a small skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot. Add minced onion and crushed red pepper. Saute 3 minutes or until tender. Remove from heat.
Stir in brown sugar, black pepper, white wine vinegar, soy sauce and sherry. Set aside.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Pour off any grease.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes over medium heat, uncovered. Add soup and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and noodles (adjust quantity to personal taste).
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.
If desired, serve noodles separately and let each guest spoon on the stroganoff.

title: applesauce oat bran muffins(low-fat)
directions: In a large bowl, stir together dry ingredients.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients until well blended.
Mix both bowls together and pour into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dice or slice potatoes.
Boil until just done.
Drain.
Put in greased casserole dish.

title: frozen chocolate sticks
directions: Advance preparation:
In saucepan, combine pudding mix and sugar; prepare according to the package directions.
Stir a moderate amount of hot pudding into egg yolks; return to remaining pudding in pan.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cover surface with waxed paper; cool.
Fold whites into pudding.
Spoon into 6 (5 ounce) paper drink cups.
Insert wooden stick into each. Freeze firm.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish at 375° for about 40 minutes. Should be set like cornbread.

title: cheese taters
directions: Cook potato slices covered with water until tender.
In a shallow casserole dish, place a layer of potatoes and a layer of cheese with salt and pepper.
When all the potatoes and cheese are layered, pour enough of the water over them to almost cover them. Place in a 350° oven until cheese is melted and slightly browned.

title: rhubarb brunch cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. In large bowl, mix and prepare cake mix according to package directions (don't forget the high altitude adjustments).
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Top with rhubarb.
Sprinkle with sugar. Pour cream over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours, or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Serve warm. Store in refrigerator.

title: crab toast
directions: Combine ingredients; spread on buttered toast rounds or English muffins.
Broil until bubbly.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Mix together and marinate chicken several hours.

title: apple muffins
directions: Cream together sugar and butter; beat in egg.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture. Stir in vanilla and apples.
Fill 12 to 14 muffin (2 1/2-inch) tins or cups to the top (if using tins, butter).
Sprinkle with topping.

title: chocolate spritz
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in bowl and beat until creamy. Blend in flour.
Use cookie gun.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 19 minutes.
Makes 12 dozen.

title: chicken and vegetable twist
directions: In skillet, fry chicken cubes until done.
Remove from skillet and cook all vegetables and garlic powder until tender, stirring often.
Stir in soup, milk and cheese.
Add macaroni and chicken. Heat thoroughly, stirring often.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugars and vanilla.
Stir dry ingredients into creamed mixture. Form into balls.
Roll in sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with back of fork to make crisscross.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: zur
directions: Cover the flour with lukewarm water.
Add a piece of sour rye bread of approximately 2 inches diameter.
Leave the mixture in a warm place for 24 hours.
When the mixture is well soured, take out the bread and pass the rest through a sieve.
Bring to a boil, 3 cups of water and slowly pour over the mixture, stirring constantly.
Leave it on low flame until it boils.
On the side, chop the bacon and the mushrooms and fry until lightly browned. Squeeze in the garlic and add both to the soup.
Serve with boiled potatoes.

title: bill's gravy
directions: Cook drippings and flour together, mashing out lumps.
Add seasonings.
Add milk, water and Kitchen Bouquet; stir and heat thoroughly.

title: cheese bread
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put 1 package rolls on bottom of pan.
Mix other ingredients and place on top of rolls.
Put other package of rolls on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: veggie stuffed flounder
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Saute all julienned vegetables in butter until tender, not overcooked.
Allow to cool to room temperature.

title: french toast
directions: Place a little oil in a skillet.
Beat eggs, cream and a pinch of salt together.
Dip bread into batter allowing batter to soak in.
Fry bread in skillet until brown; turn and fry on the other side.
Transfer to cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 4 minutes or until puffed.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour, salt, sugar, butter, and vanilla. Beat until the mixture clings together. Stir in the walnuts and mini-chips. Form the dough into 1 inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and press to about 1/4 inch thick using the bottom of a glass. If the dough sticks, dip the bottom of the glass into sugar before pressing the cookies. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until very lightly browned. Remove from the pan and coat with confectioners' sugar. Place on a rack to cool. After cookies have cooled, coat again with confectioners' sugar. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: monkey bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Add milk, shortening, salt, sugar, egg and flour.
Let stand 2 hours until double in bulk.
Roll out dough to about 1/2-inch thickness; cut into 4 diamond shapes.
Dip each piece into butter; place in tube pan.
Let each piece overlap.
Make 2 layers.
Let stand 1 hour.
Bake in moderate oven until golden brown.
Serve warm and pull apart.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mix together in a small bowl the first 4 ingredients.
Mix in another small bowl the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.
Layer on a large platter the bean dip on the bottom, the avocado mixture next, then the sour cream mixture and top with the onions, tomatoes, olives and the cheese.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: smoked sausage casserole
directions: Cut sausage into 8 pieces.
Cut sausage in half, not all the way through.
Place 1/4 slice cheese in cut in sausage.
Roll cooked lasagna noodle around sausage.
Place fold down in pan. Pour sauce over sausages.
Place 1/4 pieces cheese over sausage. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: flounder with lemon cream
directions: Preheat broiler.
Line broiler pan with foil.
Melt butter on stovetop.
In a small bowl, combine melted butter, 2 tablespoons lemon juice, 1 teaspoon lemon zest, 1/2 teaspoon tarragon, salt and pepper.
Place fish on prepared pan.
Brush lemon-butter mixture on fish.
Broil fish 4 inches from heat about 7 minutes until fish is cooked.
In mixer bowl, combine remaining 2 tablespoons lemon juice, 2 teaspoons lemon zest, 1/2 teaspoon tarragon, Dijon mustard and dry mustard.
Beat cream into mixture in a thin stream. Continue beating until cream forms soft peaks.
Serve fish topped with a dollop of the lemon cream.

title: chicken and new potatoes
directions: Brown pieces of chicken in oil.
Peel around center of each potato.
Place around chicken.
Slice carrots on top and then slice onion over all.
Turn heat to low.
Cook about 1 hour.
Use a large, heavy skillet.

title: chocolate-covered cherries
directions: Drain cherries; let dry on paper towel overnight.
In small bowl, combine butter, liqueur and corn syrup.
Stir in powdered sugar; knead until smooth.
Form a heaping 1/2 teaspoonful fondant around each cherry.
Place on waxed paper-covered cookie sheet; refrigerate.

title: pumpkin coffee cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook beef, onions, garlic and oil in heavy skillet until the onions are soft and the beef is crumbly.
Add salt, rosemary, pepper, tomato paste and hot water.
Mix well and simmer, uncovered, about 30 minutes.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Take some small leaves and some chocolate, melted gently in the oven or over a pan of hot water.
Wipe the leaves clean with a damp tissue.
Let them dry thoroughly before dipping them, upper side down, into the surface of the melted chocolate.
Lay them, chocolate side up, on a plate and leave in a cool place to set.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and salt and pepper.
Drain.
Pour rest of ingredients over ground beef and cook until well blended (1 hour).

title: california walnut pie
directions: Mix
brown
sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add corn syrup, margarine
and
salt.
Heat until margarine is melted. Beat
eggs and
vanilla
together.
Stir
into sugar mixture. Blend well. Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Add 1 cup hot water to melted shortening.
Mix 1 package yeast and 1/2 cup water.
Add 1 beaten egg to yeast mixture.
Combine all ingredients together.
Add flour.
Mix well with wire beater or electric mixer.
Place in bowl in warm place.
Cover with towel. Let rise twice its size.
Punch down.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Place rolls on it. Cover with towel; let rise again.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: aunt maggie's chocolate cake
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, eggs, shortening and sour milk with the baking soda in it.
Add the remaining ingredients to first mixture and stir.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes at 370°.
Ice right from oven with chocolate frosting. This is what keeps cake real moist.

title: chive cheese 'n tuna pie
directions: Line a 9-inch torte shell with pie pastry and chill.
Combine ingredients in given order.
Mix well.
Pour into chilled, unbaked shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine with soups, broth and chiles. Add chicken and beat well.

title: party punch
directions: Mix 3 to 4 scoops Country Time pink lemonade, orange juice (do not dilute) and sugar to taste (may use Sweet 'N Low).
Add 1 quart water to mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Add 1 quart water and stir.
Enjoy!
It is great!!

title: party chicken
directions: Split chicken breasts just enough to fold. Combine flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt, paprika and dash of pepper in a paper bag. Add chicken and shake to coat.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Place cauliflower in pan.
Top with lettuce.
Cover with Miracle Whip.
Sprinkle with sugar, cheese, onion, bacon and Cheddar cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix before serving.

title: apricot salad
directions: Make Jell-O according to package directions.
Chill until slightly thick.
Stir in mashed cream cheese, pineapple and marshmallows.
Whip Dream Whip and fold into Jell-O mixture.
Pour into large Pyrex dish and refrigerate overnight.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Prepare favorite baking powder biscuit mixture.
After rolling dough out, place apples on dough and core them.
Be sure to leave enough space between each apple to allow for wrapping dough around them.
Fill cored apples with sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Fold dough up into the apple core and turn the apples upside-down.

title: peach flan
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, nutmeg and butter together.
Sprinkle a little over an unbaked pie shell, then place fresh peach halves (with cut side down) over this.
Spread the balance of the mixture over the top to form a covering instead of crust.
Bake for 15 minutes at 450°, then turn oven down to 325°.
Bake for about 40 minutes.
Can be served warm or cold, plain or with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: fried okra
directions: Cut okra in 1-inch rounds; season to taste.
In a small bowl, beat egg; add milk.
Dip okra in mixture; roll in seasoned cornmeal.
Fry in deep fat until crisp; brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serves 4.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Cream margarine and flour together.
Add pecans and spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: butter-bite-hoe cakes
directions: Combine corn meal and boiling water; stir to blend.
In large skillet, heat 1/4-inch shortening over medium-low heat until drop of water sizzles when dropped in skillet.
Spoon batter by tablespoons into hot skillet.
Fry until golden brown.
Turn and fry on other side.
Serve with hot butter.
Makes about 10 hoe cakes.

title: beet salad
directions: Mix together.
Add salad dressing and chill.

title: sponge cake
directions: Bake in ungreased tube pan at 325° to 350° for 25 minutes; jelly roll pan at 375°.

title: lithuanian potato sausage
directions: In a skillet, fry bacon and onion until nice and brown; set aside.
In a bowl, put potatoes; add eggs, flour, salt, pepper, bacon and onion.
Mix well.
Push through sausage casing.
Lay in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.
Makes 3 nice links.

title: cornbread muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and eggs.
Stir together well. Add oil and stir thoroughly.
Pour into well-greased muffin tins. Fill 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: carol's taco appetizer
directions: Large platter with an edge to spread the ingredients.
Sour cream is spread on the bottom.
Cut up the white part of the green onion.
Cut up tomatoes to fill plate and add.
Cut up celery and add next, probably 3 or 4 stalks.
Cut up green pepper and add. Taco sauce is added on top of all of it.
Shredded Cheddar is added last.
Enjoy.

title: pea salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch glass pan put torn lettuce.
Then cut up onions over the lettuce.
Drain and add peas on top of onions. Mix the sour cream, mayonnaise and sugar; put over the top. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese, then bacon bits.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: lucille's date chocolate chip bars
directions: Pour boiling water over dates.
Add baking soda and let cool. Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and mix.
Add flour, salt and vanilla and mix.
Add date mixture and mix.
Spread in 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Cover with 6 ounce package chocolate bits and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: jello chiffon pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and sour cream in a large bowl.
Add Jell-O. Stir until smooth.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill for 2 hours. Serve.

title: burritos
directions: Brown sausage in skillet and drain.
Add beans (you will need a little of the bean juice).
Sprinkle cumin.
Stir and mash beans and sausage together into mixture.
Serve on hot flour tortillas with sour cream and hot sauce.
Roll up as burrito and enjoy!

title: sour cream enchilada casserole
directions: Combine water and 2 tablespoons picante sauce in a large shallow dish.
Place tortillas in picante sauce mixture; let stand 5 minutes.
Cook ground beef and onion in a heavy skillet until brown; drain off drippings.
Stir in salt, pepper, cumin, chili powder, garlic powder, olives and 1/4 cup picante sauce; simmer meat mixture 5 minutes.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
