Gradually stir in milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat and add sour cream; stir until well blended.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning.
Spread this mixture onto a serving plate.
Pour taco sauce on top of sour cream mixture.
Top with onion, cucumber, lettuce and tomato. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chinese kitchen soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook celery and onion with garlic and ginger in butter until tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes or until done. Stir occasionally. Serve with additional soy sauce.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: 3 step cheesecake
directions: Step 1:
In mixer, add first four ingredients.
Mix until well blended.

title: broccolini veggie toss
directions: In saucepot in enough boiling water to cover, cook broccolini 5 minutes; drain.
In a large skillet over medium-high heat, cook garlic and pepper in oil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add broccolini, lemon pepper, oregano and wine; cover.
Cook 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with pine nuts.
Makes 8 servings.

title: italian-style garlic spread for bread
directions: Beat together all ingredients.
Spread on sliced bread.
Place in toaster oven.
Heat 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Store remaining spread in a covered jar in refrigerator.
Will keep for 1 month.

title: chili
directions: Mix all together in a large skillet or saucepan.
Cook for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Saute onion in margarine.
Cook Minute rice. Mix broccoli, onion and rice with soup and Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 305 degrees until golden brown.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cook until peanut butter and sugar are dissolved.
Add corn flakes.
Spread in buttered pan.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: marinade for meat
directions: Mix all ingredients together stirring gently.
Pour over meat; cover, refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Turn meat a few times.

title: date and nut ice cream pie
directions: Stir ice cream until softened.
Spread on bottom of baked pie shell.
Place in freezer.

title: holiday crunch
directions: Spray 3-quart casserole with Pam.
Cook macaroni according to package instructions.
Brown ground meat and drain after cooking. Combine mushroom soup, chopped tomatoes with juice, browned meat, cheese, green pepper and drained macaroni.
Pour half of mixture in casserole and put 1/2 can of French fried onions, then add the remainder of mixture and place in 350° oven and cover.
Bake for 30 minutes; add the rest of the French fried onions and bake for additional 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Sprinkle potatoes with half the salt.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onion, garlic and remaining salt; fold in potatoes. Pour into buttered casserole; top with cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: omelet with cheese sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, cook soup and cream over low heat until warm, stirring occasionally. In a small bowl, beat the eggs, salt and pepper. Stir in chilies. Melt butter in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat. Add egg mixture. As the eggs set, lift edges, letting uncooked portion flow underneath. When eggs are completely set, remove from the heat. Fold omelet in half. Cut into three wedges. Serve with the cheese sauce. Refrigerate any leftover sauce. Yield: 3 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: In a heavy pot, heat cooking oil. Be sure there is sufficient cooking oil to allow hush puppies to float. Mix all ingredients well. Drop by teaspoon into hot oil. Hush puppies will puff up as they fry.
When completely browned, remove from oil to drain on paper towels.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Heat mashed berries to simmering.
Cook gently for 3 minutes; strain through fine sieve.
Be sure to extract all juice.
To juice, add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
In saucepan, mix the cornstarch and 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Boil, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Add the butter, 1 cup sugar and the lemon juice; cool.
Arrange a layer of fresh, halved berries in bottom of pie shell.
Spoon glaze over. Continue making layers this way until you get to the top.
Set in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream.

title: icebox strawberry pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, lemonade and strawberries together. Stir in 8-ounce Cool Whip last. Pour into prepared crust. Spread the 12-ounce Cool Whip on top and refrigerate overnight.

title: pickled beets
directions: Pack beets tightly into a quart jar.
Boil sugar and vinegar; pour over beets and seal.
Let set in refrigerator overnight before eating.

title: lemon gooey
directions: *I use Duncan Hines Supreme lemon cake mix.

title: corn corn bread
directions: Mix everything together, except cheese.
Put in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Last 10 minutes, sprinkle with cheese.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough out onto a pizza sheet.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil in heavy pot. Add butter. Cook until candy forms soft ball in cold water. Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until candy thickens.
Pour in small 6 x 10-inch oblong dish (which has been lightly buttered). When candy cools, cut in squares.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; pour into baking dish and top with the remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine until soft.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken supreme
directions: To begin, flatten the chicken by placing it between two sheets of waxed paper and pound it with a mallet.
Sprinkle the chicken with the salt and pepper.

title: emmett's cuckoo clock cocoa mix
directions: In a glass jar or airtight container mix all ingredients and mix well.
Cover and store until needed.
Add 2 tablespoons of mix to 1 cup of water for a quick cup of hot cocoa.
Makes about 34 servings.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Cook potatoes and cool.
Grate potatoes, then add unbeaten eggs.
Stir until blended.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Pour by spoonful and fry until golden brown.

title: "uncrust" custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly. Add sugar, spices and flour. Beat. Add milk. Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate. Bake in oven at 370° for 30 minutes. Test with knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: lasagne
directions: Cut up Mozzarella.
Brown meat, remove fat, add spices, tomatoes and ketchup and simmer 30 minutes.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water with a bit of oil until tender.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Place 1/2 noodles in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle 1/2 cheese and cover with 1/2 sauce.
Repeat layers. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt. Bring to a boil, then let cool to 125°. Sift together about 3 cups flour, baking powder and soda. Add yeast to 1/2 cup warm water. Add to milk mixture, then add the remaining flour. Mix well. Knead until it's easy to handle. My Mom always said, "Knead until it feels like a baby's bottom." Put in an oiled or buttered pan or bowl. Cover and let rise at room temperature until doubled in bulk. Punch down and refrigerate 3 hours to 10 days (covered tightly). Generally needs to be punched down every day or so.

title: company potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, combine potatoes, undiluted soups, sour cream, milk and onion.
Stir until well mixed and season with salt, pepper and dill weed.
Turn into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle evenly with grated cheese and paprika. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, until browned on top and bubbly. Serves 8 to 10.

title: mamaw's fruit cake cookies
directions: Soak fruit in wine while sifting flour and spices together. Add fruit to flour mixture.
Add pecans.
Refrigerate overnight. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet (1 tsp. for each cookie).
Bake at 250 degrees for about 20 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, beat egg yolks with Eagle Brand milk.
Pour into prepared pastry shell; bake 20 minutes.
Cool.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In hot oil, cook onions, celery and garlic until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, sugar, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 45 minutes; thicken with cornstarch.
Add shrimp and green pepper.
Cover and simmer until done, about 5 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar. Spread over bottom of 2 pie crusts. Spread sliced peaches over cream cheese mixture; set aside. Mix 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and water together. Bring to a boil and add Jell-O, mixing well. Cool slightly, then spread over peaches. Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic in saucepan until done.
Add tomato sauce and cook down.
Mix cottage cheese, parsley flakes, salt, oregano, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Layer noodles, cottage cheese mixture, then ground beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: white fudge
directions: Let sugar, syrup, milk and butter come to a boil; boil for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and walnuts.
Put pan in cool water and beat until it begins to get hard, approximately 1 minute.
Pour into a greased pan.
Cut immediately.

title: pressure cooker round steak
directions: Recipe amounts are for a 2 1/2 to 4-quart cooker.
Double the amounts for a 6 to 8-quart cooker.

title: country pie
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, pepper, seasonings and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Spread in greased 10-inch pie plate, forming a shell.
Mix rice, cheese and remaining sauce.
Place in meat shell.
Sprinkle top with additional cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tangy russian chicken
directions: For sauce, combine Russian dressing, soup mix and preserves. Mix well.
Pour over 6 chicken breasts in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread in cream about 5 minutes. Cook onion in one Tbsp of butter until tender. Mix cream cheese, egg, bread crumb mixture, onion, parsley, salt, pepper, spices and meat.

title: date nut bars
directions: Heat together margarine, pitted dates, maraschino cherries and sugar. Stir constantly over medium heat until it becomes soft paste. Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies cereal and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Portion by level tablespoonfuls on waxed paper. Shape into balls. Cool.

title: flank steak teriyaki barbecue
directions: Combine oil, soy sauce, honey, vinegar, onions, garlic and ginger.
Pour over flank steak and marinate 4 hours or more; turn occasionally.
Barbecue steak* over hot coals, turning once until done to your preference, about 5 minutes on each side for medium-rare.
Baste occasionally with marinade.
Carve in thin slices, cutting on the diagonal from top to bottom of steak as for London broil.
Makes 4 servings.

title: roast beef
directions: Flour roast. Brown in butter and pepper. Combine soup, onion mix and wine. Pour over browned roast. Bake 2 1/2 hours at 325°. Saut mushrooms and add to roast last 30 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes with marshmallows
directions: Mix all and bake until firm.
Add marshmallows; then finish cooking.

title: edwards' oyster and virginia ham(a colonial seafood delicacy served in patty shells!)
directions: Bake patty shells by directions on package; cool.
Dissolve bouillon in warm water and set aside.
Drain oysters and reserve liquor.
Melt butter over low heat; stir in flour and allow to bubble for one minute.
Do not brown.
Remove from heat and slowly stir in bouillon, oyster liquor and cream.
Return to low heat and stir until thickened.
Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and onion salt.
Remove from heat, cover and set aside.
Saute oysters in butter only until edges curl and oysters are just firm.
Drain. Stir oysters and ham into sauce and heat gently over low heat. Spoon into patty shells and top with cracked pepper and chopped parsley.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: the best brownies(as tested by tr. debby's 1st grade:  1992-93)
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in a saucepan.
Stir.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and blend until smooth.

title: cheese ball
directions: Get cheese at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Roll in nuts or paprika. Makes 2 logs or balls.

title: daffodil cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box, using a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool cake and poke holes in it an inch apart.
Cook pineapple and sugar, about 5 minutes.
Cool and pour over cake. Fix pudding according to directions on package.
Pour over the pineapple mixture.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with pecans and refrigerate.

title: cottage cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If mixture is too soft, more crumbs may be added.
Form into balls about the size of a large walnut and drop into deep fat.
Cook until they turn a deep, golden brown.
At this stage, they may be stored in the freezer for future use or place in a shallow casserole; pour sauce over them and bake in medium oven for 1/2 hour.

title: chuck wagon beef bake
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add vegetables to meat and simmer until tender.
Add tomato paste, water, chili powder, salt, paprika and beans; simmer while making topping.

title: wacky cake
directions: This cake can be mixed right in the pan, or if you wish, in a bowl.

title: oven barbecued steak
directions: Combine all but steak in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pound steak.
Cut into serving pieces.
Place in pan.
Pour sauce over meat.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Good barbecue sauce for chicken and pork chops, too!

title: sausage-spinach lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large 10-inch skillet over medium heat, brown sausage; drain off fat.
Spread a thin layer of the spaghetti sauce in the bottom of a 3-quart oblong baking dish. Stir remaining sauce and Italian seasonings into sausage; set aside.
In a large mixer bowl at low speed, beat Ricotta, spinach, Parmesan and eggs until blended.
In baking dish, layer half of the noodles, half of the sausage mixture and half of the spinach mixture; repeat.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crab spread
directions: Combine dressing mix, mayonnaise and Tabasco.
Add cream cheese and mix well.
Stir in crab meat.
Cover and chill.
Best when made a day before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with melted butter, followed by brown sugar.
Then place pineapple and cherries in.
Mix and blend cake mix, eggs, water and oil.
Pour into prepared pan and bake slowly at 250° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Check to see if done.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Empty yeast into large bowl; add water and dissolve.
Add eggs, butter, salt and sugar.
Stir well; add first 2 cups flour and mix well.
Add rest of flour.
Let rise until double in bulk (flour board).
Roll and cut about the size of small biscuits.
Place on baking sheet.
Melt butter and brush on tops before letting rise second time.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: ernie's stove top meatloaf
directions: Mix meat loaf ingredients.
Shape into a loaf in a large skillet.
Pour sauce ingredients around and over loaf.
Cook on top of stove until done (I cook on medium for close to 1 hour). The tomatoes make a wonderful gravy.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients in bottom of dish like crust. Beat confectioners sugar, eggs and 2 stick of butter with electric mixer for 5 to 6 minutes or until fluffy.
Pour this mixture over the crust.
Slice bananas and cover mixture; add pineapple (drained) over bananas; cover mixture with cool whip.
Spread chopped nuts and cherries over top.
Refrigerate.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins in water until plump, about 3 minutes.
Cool. Sift next 6 ingredients together.
Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in raisins and leftover water. Gradually add flour mixture.
Drop by tablespoon or teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 100 small cookies or 3 dozen large ones.

title: sugar cookies ii
directions: Melt margarine in Pyrex bowl in microwave, just to liquid stage.
Add sugar; mix.
Add egg; mix.
Add milk and vanilla; mix. Gradually add dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover lightly and refrigerate one hour at least.
Can make ahead.
Store tightly in refrigerator up to one week.
When ready to bake, divide dough to roll out on floured cutting board or surface into 1/8 to 1/4 inch thickness, using cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Overbaking will cause browning on edges.
Cool on racks.

title: irish apple cake
directions: Rub flour and margarine together.
Add sugar; mix well. Gradually add beaten eggs and apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix sugar, molasses and shortening.
Add water and 2 cups flour, mixed and sifted with soda, salt and spices.
Add enough additional flour to roll.
Cut and bake in moderate oven (325° to 350°).

title: rick's cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan and sprinkle with pecans. Place frozen rolls on top of pecans.
Sprinkle instant pudding mix over the rolls.
Melt butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix and pour over frozen rolls.
Let rise overnight.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Take out of pan while hot.
Makes 24.

title: carrot soup
directions: In soup pot or large kettle, saute onion and garlic in margarine until soft.
Mix carrots, potatoes, salt, pepper, bay leaf and thyme.
Add to pot.
Mix well.
Add chicken broth and enough water so vegetables are covered.
Simmer 30 minutes. Remove bay leaf and puree soup in blender.
Makes 11 (1 cup) servings.

title: rosettes
directions: Sift flour.
Beat eggs until light, add milk, sugar, salt, vanilla and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Heat oil.
Dip iron into batter being careful not to get batter on top of iron or it will not release from iron when put in grease.
Fry until brown, drain on paper towel and dust with powdered sugar.
Good also with honey drizzled over them and then powdered sugar.

title: candied pecans
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan mix sugar, milk, Karo and salt.
Cook to soft ball stage, 238°.
Add nuts and stir until creamy.
Quickly turn out on waxed paper and separate with fork.

title: witches brew
directions: Mix in a punch bowl.

title: creamy peanut butter candy
directions: Mix
sugar,
butter and milk;
cook for 6 to 8 minutes. Take off stove
and
stir
in
cup
peanut butter and 1 jar marshmallow cream.	Add 2 cups pecans.
Spread on cookie sheet and let cool.

title: healthy pasta
directions: Pour tomato sauce and tomatoes into a pot.
Heat with a low flame.
Slice garlic thinly and saute in small amount of olive oil for 5 minutes on a low flame until garlic begins to brown.
Tilt saute pan and move garlic to one side with oil on the other side. Remove garlic and put into sauce mixture.
Add a handful of oregano and basil.
Stir all in.
Cook until very hot, stirring regularly. Prepare favorite pasta the way you like it and use this very low fat sauce as you like it.

title: brie with sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Remove the rind from the Brie with a sharp knife and put the Brie on a serving plate.
In a small bowl, combine the parsley, the Parmesan, the sun-dried tomatoes, the garlic and the basil. Add the reserved oil and combine the mixture well.
Spread the mixture over the Brie and let the Brie stand for 1 hour before serving.
Serve the Brie with the crackers.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick oleo and graham crackers; pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat
eggs,
sticks
margarine
and powdered sugar for no less than
minutes.
Spread this mixture over graham cracker crust and cover
with
a single layer of sliced bananas. Spread crushed
pineapple (drained) over bananas and cover with container of
Cool Whip, then sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cut up cherries,
if
desired.
Sprinkle over top.
For best results, refrigerate overnight.
Serves 12.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Make balls and roll into mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Place into Bundt pan.
Melt butter and brown sugar together.
Then pour over the rolls.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Then invert onto a plate.

title: stroganoff balls
directions: Mix veal, soup and milk.
Make into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift flour, meal, salt and baking powder together.
Add egg and milk and mix into dry ingredients.
Add chopped onion.
Drop from tablespoon into deep, hot fat.
Fry until golden brown.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine flour, butter and 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Pat into 8-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Combine eggs, granulated sugar, baking powder and lemon juice.
Pour over crust and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and sprinkle with sifted powdered sugar. Cut into squares.

title: beans
directions: Rinse beans thoroughly and soak overnight.
Rinse beans again and cover with water.
Add broth powder, garlic, oil, salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Last 30 minutes add chopped onions. Onions may be sauteed in small amount of butter before adding to beans for extra flavor.

title: mom beck's old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together until well combined.
Pour into greased and floured baking pan in a 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: carolyn's chicken delight
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in rice, salt and pepper.
Lay chicken pieces on top of rice.
Pour soup mix over the chicken.
Pour water around edges of pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for one hour.
Turn oven off, let set in oven for one hour.

title: mexican style potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch slices; set aside.
Cook bacon in skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Add salt and chili powder to skillet, stirring well.
Add potatoes to skillet; gently stir to coat with seasoning.
Spoon potatoes into a lightly greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle with bacon and parsley.
Cover; bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 6 servings.

title: old fashioned crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, butter and cream of tartar like pie dough.
Take out and reserve crumbs for top.
Add buttermilk, baking soda and cinnamon to the remaining crumbs.
Makes 2 layers. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: hurricane cake
directions: Prepare 9 x 13 cake pan with non-stick cooking spray. Pre-heat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine 1 cup of chopped pecans with 1 cup coconut.
Sprinkle evenly over bottom of pan.
Prepare cake as directed on box.
Pour batter over nuts, DO NOT MIX.
In mixing bowl, beat butter, powdered sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on top of batter avoiding sides of pan.
Bake for 55 minutes or until cake is done.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients and spoon into well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan and cool.
Top with glaze.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine the Parmesan cheese, flour, paprika, salt, pepper and milk.
In a separate bowl mix the egg and melted margarine.
Dip the chicken in the egg mixture, then in the cheese mixture.
Place in a baking pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: non-crumbling cornbread
directions: Mix together the eggs, sugar, buttermilk or sour milk and vegetable oil or melted margarine.
Add corn meal.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to corn meal mixture.
Place in greased and floured 8-inch square or 9-inch round pan.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Check with cake tester to be sure it is done.

title: mock apple pie(no apples needed)
directions: Roll out bottom crust and fit into 9-inch pie pan.
Break Ritz crackers coarsely into pastry lined pan.
Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar in saucepan.
Boil gently for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Cool.
Pour syrup over crackers; dot generously with butter or oleo and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with top crust.
Trim and flute edges together.
Cut slit in top of crust to let steam escape.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes until crust is crisp and golden.
Serve warm.

title: beer-cheese fondue
directions: Have the cheeses at room temperature.

title: hard times coffee
directions: Mix well 2 quarts wheat bran with 1 pint yellow corn meal. Add 3 well beaten eggs and 1 cup best sorghum molasses.
Beat well.
Spread on pan and put to dry in oven.
Use great care by stirring often while it is browning.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, salt, sugar and baking soda together.
Mix pumpkin, oil, water, eggs and spices together and combine with dry ingredients.
Do not overmix.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake in two well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Turn out and let cool on wire racks.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: italiano main dish soup
directions: Shape beef into 18 meatballs.
In a large saucepan, brown meatballs and cook onion with garlic and oregano in shortening until tender.
Add cabbage.
Cook until tender.
Add bean with bacon soup. Gradually stir in water. Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Heat. Stir occasionally. Serve with cheese.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: bubble up pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine pepper, onion, mushrooms, olives and spaghetti sauce.
Press garlic over mixture and mix well.
Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Arrange half of the biscuit pieces evenly over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bottom won't be completely covered.
Spread with half of the sauce mixture. Sprinkle with half of the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake 28 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into 8 squares.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: crabmeat and sherry hors d'oeuvres
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Blend ingredients together into smooth spreading consistency.
Spread evenly on muffins.
Quarter each muffin (64 pieces).
Place on cookie sheet (they should not touch) and freeze uncovered one hour.
When frozen, place in plastic bags.
To serve, place on cookie sheet and bake at 450° until lightly browned on edges (approximately 18 minutes).
Enjoy!

title: orange jello salad
directions: Combine egg, sugar, pineapple syrup and flour.
Cook until thickened.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Add egg mixture and pour over jell.
Jell.
Serve cool.

title: mojave fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit ingredients together.
Mix the orange rind into the salad dressing and toss with fruit.

title: sweet yeast bread
directions: Mix yeast in water with pinch of sugar.
Let stand until double in size. Combine remainder of sugar, salt and 4 cups of the flour in a large bowl.
Make a well and drop in eggs, yeast mixture and milk.
Mix with a spoon. Add butter and more flour. Mix with hands.
Keep adding flour until able to handle.
Knead. Put in buttered bowl and let rise until double in size, approximately 2 hours.
Punch down and allow to rise 15 minutes. Form into desired shapes and let rise approximately 1 hour. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in milk and water. Let stand 5 minutes. Add egg, shortening, salt, remaining sugar and enough flour to form a soft dough. Turn onto a floured surface. Knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.

title: fruit fantasy
directions: Place all fruit in a casserole.
Mix well. Combine mandarin orange juice and remaining ingredients in a small bowl. Mix well. Pour liquid mixture over fruit.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cheesy spinach dip
directions: Cut slice from top of bread, remove center, leaving 1-inch shell.
Cut removed bread into bite size pieces; reserve.
Brush inside of shell and pieces with melted margarine.
Place on cookie sheet with reserved bread and brown in oven.

title: cheesecake
directions: Melt butter.
Add graham cracker crumbs, mixed with 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Blend and pack mixture in bottom and sides of greased 9-inch pie plate.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix well the bananas, eggs, shortening, sugar and vanilla. Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes for layer cake, 45 to 50 minutes for 9 x 13-inch oblong.
Frost as desired.

title: 5 cup fruit salad
directions: Mix together.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: In large bowl combine pecans, crushed graham crackers, raisins, cherries and pineapple. In large saucepan combine marshmallows, milk and butter. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted. Pour over pecan mixture and mix well. Shape into 1 inch balls and roll in coconut. Moist hands frequently with water help shape the cookie balls.

title: okra and rice
directions: Fry bacon, onion and bell pepper together.
Add okra and salt and pepper to taste.
When okra gets crispy, add rice and a few dashes of soy sauce.
Very good!

title: mango bread
directions: Mix flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and set aside.
Beat the eggs while gradually adding the sugar.
Add the oil and vanilla.
To the egg mixture, add 1 cup of flour mixture and 1 cup mangos. Repeat until all is blended.
Add nuts, raisins and coconut. Spoon into 4 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: great grandma's homemade german noodles(or helmkamp's famous noodles)
directions: Beat eggs and milk together; beat well.
Work butter into this mixture using fork to blend.
Add enough flour to thicken for rolling.
Knead on floured board.
Roll onto thinly floured board. Dry by hanging on the back of chair, 1 to 2 hours.
Sprinkle with flour and roll up real tight as for a jelly roll.
Flour and cut into thin slices.
Pull slices apart.
Cook noodles, uncovered, in salted boiling water for 5 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally; drain.
Put the noodles back in the pot with 1/4 cup of milk and heat.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Serve with main course.

title: hearty chicken stew
directions: Toss chicken with flour, salt and pepper.
Melt butter in a large skillet. Add chicken (with excess flour). Saute 3 minutes to brown. Add onion and celery. Saute 3 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Serves 8.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Mix bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese; add according to your tastes (dried parsley flakes, oregano, garlic powder, salt and pepper).
Dip chicken in beaten eggs and then crumb mixture.
Put in well-greased shallow pan.
Cover each piece of chicken with lemon butter.
Sprinkle chicken with sesame seed (optional).
Bake at 350°.
Cover with foil for first 1/2 hour, uncovered for second 1/2 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in large skillet.
Add onion, garlic salt and oregano.
Cook until onion is tender.
Add soup and vinegar; simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In a medium bowl, mix the Ricotta cheese, egg, parsley flakes, sugar and a dash of pepper.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer noodles, cheese mixture, meat sauce and Mozzarella.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle final layer with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Slice berries and place in crust.
Cook sugar, cornstarch and 7-Up until mixture thickens.
Add salt.
Mix in jello and cool. Pour over berries and chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the soups and sour cream.
Put chicken in casserole dish; cover with soup mixture.
Top with the Pepperidge Farm herb dressing.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: caramel sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange sweet potatoes in baking dish. In small saucepan over medium heat, combine remaining ingredients; heat to boiling; reduce heat to low and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour mixture over sweet potatoes.
Bake 20 minutes, or until potatoes are well glazed, basting often.
To serve, spoon syrup over potatoes.
Serves about 6.

title: shoo-fly bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine 2 cups flour and brown sugar. Cut in shortening with pastry blender until fine crumbs.
Remove 1/2 cup crumbs and set aside. To the remaining crumbs, add 1 cup flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Stir until well blended.
Mix together egg, molasses and water. Add to crumb mixture and stir by hand just until blended.
Pour into well-greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. Sprinkle 1/2 cup reserved crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until tests done.

title: bean salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix all the ingredients together.
Let set in a refrigerator overnight. Salt and pepper to own taste.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Mix milk and salt.
Dip fish in salted milk.
Mix together bread crumbs and paprika.
Roll fish in bread crumbs.
Place fish side by side in oiled, shallow baking dish.
Drizzle melted butter over fish.
Bake at 525° for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish is golden and flakes easily with fork.
Watch closely.

title: fluffy pumpkin pie
directions: Put marshmallows, pumpkin and spices in top of a double boiler.
Heat and stir until marshmallows are melted.
Mix well and let cool, 45 minutes to 1 hour at room temperature or overnight.
Stir in 1/3 cup whipping cream.
Carefully fold in remaining cream.
Pour in a baked 9-inch pie shell.

title: viennese pot roast
directions: Double a 5-foot length of foil.
Place on broiler pan.
Place roast on foil; brown under broiler.
Combine remaining ingredients; spoon half of sauce under roast and remaining sauce on top.
Seal foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: chili frankfurter bake
directions: Cut 4 frankfurters in half in diagonal slices.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter in a large skillet.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and chili seasoning to skillet mixture.
Stir.
Add cooked macaroni.
Spoon into baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Make diagonal slits in remaining 6 franks and arrange on top of macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch pan.

title: dump cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Dump pineapple and pie filling in pan.
Spread evenly.
Dump dry cake mix and spread evenly over pineapple and pie filling.
Sprinkle pecans over mix.
Place pats of margarine over top.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9-inch glass pie plate with nonstick
cooking spray; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine broccoli, cottage cheese, onion, egg substitute, margarine and salt until blended.
Stir in cornmeal.
Scrape mixture into prepared pie plate.
Smooth to make even layer.
Bake for 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: farmers casserole
directions: Preheat oil to 350°.
Place potatoes in 9 x 13 oblong baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese, ham and onions. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over all.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before baking. Bake, uncovered, for 55 to 60 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, onion and flour. Add egg. Gradually beat in milk. Drop by spoonful into hot oil until golden brown.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain fruit juice.
Add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups. Bring to a boil and pour over jello and stir to dissolve.
Cool. Whip cream cheese until smooth.
Then add Coca-Cola and cream cheese to jello mixture and whip until well combined.
Let the jello congeal; before it hardens, add pineapple and nuts.

title: rice consomme
directions: Melt butter, then add onion, green pepper and rice.
Cook until rice mixture begins to brown.
Then add consomme, water, salt and pepper.
Steam under low heat for 30 minutes.

title: oriental salad dressing
directions: Mix all together in quart jar.

title: macaroni-ham-cheese salad
directions: Cook macaroni. Toss macaroni, ham, cheese, vegetables, salt, pepper and mayonnaise. Serve on lettuce and garnish with eggs.

title: pastry
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Add shortening and mix to make dough. Add water as needed, one tablespoon at a time.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pie shells.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and boiling water and sprinkle with onion flakes.
Set aside to cool.
Add tomato soup and cream cheese to Jell-O.
Fold in mayonnaise, celery and shrimp.
Refrigerate.
